title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Cut 6 tortillas in 1/2-inch wide strips.
Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons of hot oil.
Add next 10 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Add strips and cheese.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with reserved tortilla strips and chips.

title: milk custard pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Grease pie plate. Line pie plate with dough, then put corn flakes on top of dough. When baking pies it helps when corn flakes are put on top of dough before putting filling of pie.
Pour in the mixture, then sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well and bake in greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except last two. Cover with corn flakes and butter and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: apple-dapple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda, pecans, apples and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While still warm, glaze.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place corned beef in a lightly greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Dot with dressing. Spread sauerkraut over top; sprinkle with cheese. Toss bread crumbs with butter; sprinkle over cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: regal chocolate sauce
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar and water.
Cook to medium soft boil (236°).
Remove from heat and add chocolate.
Stir until melted. Add vanilla.
Slowly add evaporated milk.
Mix thoroughly. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cocoa puff
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/2 the sugar gradually, continue to beat until very stiff and smooth.
Sift cocoa with rest of sugar. Add gradually, continuing to beat all the while. Finally beat in vanilla.
Pile into dessert dishes.
Serve with cream.

title: aunt hooey's banana cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs together.
Add mashed bananas.
Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to wet.
Mix and pour in sour milk.
Add chopped nuts when almost mixed enough.
Bake in 2 (8 x 8 x 2-inch) pans or 1 (7 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch) pan at 350°.

title: molasses krinkles
directions: Combine butter, eggs, sugar and shortening; mix.
Add soda, salt, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Mix in the molasses and then add the flour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice of cans of fruit and add enough water to make 3 1/2 cups.
Cook until thick, cool.
Then add oranges, pineapple, maraschino cherries and bananas. You can also add diced apples (Red or Yellow Delicious).

title: white chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk with a wire whisk for 2 minutes.
Pour into baked and cooled pie crust.
Place in refrigerator for about 5 minutes.
Then stir the topping and then spread whipped topping on top of pie.
Garnish with grated chocolate candy bar, if desired. Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: down and dirty tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on package; mix in tuna and cream of mushroom soup.
Add any or all of the other ingredients if desired.
Be sure it is well mixed, then serve.
Preparation time:
Approximately 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in one pot and noodles in another pot for 20 minutes.
Combine noodles and chicken.
Add cream of mushroom soup, saltine crackers, mushrooms, butter and peas.
Add chicken broth.
Place in oven and bake 30 to 40 minutes, until crispy on top, at setting of 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked eggs in half lengthwise.
Mash egg yolks. Stir in 3 tablespoons mayonnaise, salt, mustard, vinegar, pepper and celery seed.
Spoon egg yolk mixture back into whites evenly. Arrange on plate and chill before serving.

title: garlic-dill pickles
directions: Clean cucumbers carefully.
Cut 1/4 inch off both ends of cucumbers.
Mix water, vinegar and salt in Dutch oven; heat until boiling.
Place 2 cloves of garlic, 1 dill head and onion slice in each of the 6 sterilized quart jars.
Pack cucumbers in jars, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Cover with boiling mixture, leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Wipe rims, seal and process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until medium done; rinse in ice water.
Arrange layers of carrot, green pepper and onion in a bowl or container.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring until thoroughly blended.
Pour marinade over carrot mixture and refrigerate until flavor is absorbed. Serves 12.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in advance. Chill and store in refrigerator.
Use on all kinds of salads.

title: biscuit
directions: Sift flour into bowl.
Add shortening.
Take 2 knives and cut shortening into dry flour.
It will look very lumpy.
Add buttermilk, a very little at a time, until you have a fairly stiff dough.
Sift flour onto wax paper or dough board.
Pour dough out of bowl onto floured wax paper.
Knead dough by turning over and punching dough down each time.
Work like this until you can roll dough out with dough roller.
Cut into biscuits with biscuit cutter.
Place in Pam sprayed pan.
Cook at 450° until brown.

title: 7-up pineapple salad
directions: Melt gelatin, cheese and marshmallows in double boiler. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm. Serve.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice steak thin.
Dice bell pepper, carrots and celery.
Cook steak then add ingredients.
Cook on low until done.
Serve over rice.
Top with chow mein noodles and soy sauce.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and milk.
Melt shortening and chocolate together.
Then beat for 2 minutes.
Add baking powder, 1/2 cup milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil the broccoli and drain.
Boil 1 cup of rice until dry. Melt 1 stick of margarine.
Pour it into the bowl with chicken soup, mix well.
Add the Cheez Whiz.
Add just a little bit of water.
Next add the cooked rice and broccoli.
Bake in an oven for 15 or 20 minutes until brown (at 350°).

title: mandarin orange dinner salad
directions: Put a square of foil on work surface.
Stir nuts and sugar in a small pan over medium heat 5 minutes until most sugar melts and starts to turn golden.
Pour on foil to cool.
Divide lettuce into 4 salad bowls.
Top with oranges and onions.
Break up clumps of almonds.
Add to salads.
Mix oil, honey and vinegar.
Drizzle over salads.
Sprinkle parsley on top.

title: all-bran refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix lard in cup of boiling water.
Add all-bran, salt and sugar; stir until lard is melted.
Let cool.
Add yeast that has been dissolved in cup of lukewarm water, then add eggs.
Let all cool.
Add flour; beat thoroughly.
Put in covered container. Place in refrigerator overnight.
Knead well.
Make rolls out; let stand 2 hours in warm place, then cook until brown at 300°.

title: tomato bean combo
directions: Combine cut green beans, chopped tomatoes and chopped onion. Blend together sour cream and Italian salad dressing; add to bean mixture and toss lightly.
Chill at least 2 to 3 hours.
At serving time, spoon salad into romaine lined salad bowl.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: one dish meal
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover while baking.

title: best baked beans
directions: Combine
pork
and
beans, sugar, Worcestershire, chili powder, molasses,
chili sauce and vinegar in a crock-pot with lid.
Cook on
high
for
several hours or on low overnight or most of
the
day.
Add crumbled bacon bits, if desired before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended. Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.

title: best ever chocolate cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add sifted flour with cocoa and salt alternately with buttermilk. Add soda and water. Grease and flour a Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by teaspoonful and bake at 350°.

title: new chicken supreme
directions: Wash chicken well and place in large pot. Cover with water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer until chicken is very tender, about 1 hour. Remove chicken and let cool. Remove skin and bones; dice chicken. Reserve stock. (Can be prepared ahead, covered and refrigerated.) Skim fat from chicken stock and discard. Tear bread into cubes and set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine celery, onion, salt, pepper, sage, baking powder and eggs. Mix well with a fork to break up eggs. Add diced chicken, bread cubes, milk and 1 1/2 cups reserved stock. (Save leftover stock for another use.) Toss ingredients lightly but thoroughly to combine.

title: green surprise
directions: This is a one bowl recipe.
Mix all items together and chill.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add hominy, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Put crushed Fritos on top. Place in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt
butter in cake pan;
sprinkle with brown sugar, evenly. Drain the pineapple, but save the juice. Arrange in pan, with
the
cherries
in
the
holes
of pineapple. Add sifted flour, baking
powder and salt in a bowl. Stir in sugar.
Add shortening
and milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and
egg.
Beat
2 or more minutes. Pour carefully over pineapple.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: soft honey cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream the shortening and sugar.
Add honey and eggs; beat well.
Add raisins.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk; chill.
Roll 1/2-inch thick; cut in rounds or squares.
Bake on greased pan in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Space well apart, as they puff in baking.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Mix ingredients in a medium bowl.
Let cool and set for 2 hours. Enjoy!

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, and salt over med. heat.
Gradually add the milk.
Cook and stir until mixture boils and thickens.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Separate eggs, reserving whites for meringue.
stir 3 yolks slightly and stir a small amount of hot mixture into.
Then return to hot mixture and cook 2 minutes stirring constantly.

title: beer batter for fish or chicken
directions: Beat well.
Let stand for 20 minutes, then add 3/4 bottle of stale beer (beer must be opened at least 6 hours or overnight). Dip fish or chicken in flour, then in batter, then fry in hot grease.

title: apple nut pound cake
directions: Blend the sugar, Wesson oil and eggs.
Knead with spoon.
Add flour.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour ingredients in greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apricot sweet potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes and arrange in buttered casserole.
Mix brown sugar, cornstarch, apricot nectar and juice of apricots. Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Add orange juice, cinnamon, pecans and 1 stick oleo. Stir until
melted.
Add apricots and spoon mixture over potatoes.
Bake 3 hours in 300° oven or until syrup is thick.

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and chill.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: whoopie pies(cookies)
directions: Cream together lard, sugar and eggs.
Add cocoa, soda, salt, baking powder and flour alternately with milk or buttermilk and hot water.
Put on cookie sheet by spoonfuls and bake.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Combine cheese and onion.
Fill green chilies, carefully to avoid breaking.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Dip stuffed chili into batter and fry in deep fat until golden brown.
If fresh green chilies are not available, canned ones may be used.

title: enchilada chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the soups, milk, chicken, enchilada sauce and chilies; mix well.
Cook until heated through. Garnish with sour cream and nacho chips.

title: anything goes pasta salad(make the night before serving.)
directions: Quantity of ingredients is your choice.
Add all and pour dressing over.
Mix and let set overnight.

title: apple salad bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve on crisp lettuce greens.
Tasty, colorful and easy to
prepare.

title: nut fingers
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into balls or finger shapes. Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
The nut fingers or balls will look white even after cooking.
Let cool slightly. Roll in powdered sugar and re-roll, if desired.

title: cheesy stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut tops from peppers and remove all seeds.
In a large pan, cover peppers with water and boil 8 minutes.

title: spinach-cheese pie(spanakopitta, greek name)
directions: Wash the spinach well; tear it into bite size pieces, and discard the stems.
Steam the spinach over boiling water for 8 minutes.
(Or microwave in a large bowl for about one minute.) Drain well and pat dry on paper towels.

title: corn flake bars
directions: Melt peanut butter and chips over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Pour over corn flakes.
Mix well and press into 8-inch square pan.
Cut when cool.

title: bologna bowl
directions: Fold cheese in half 2 times.
Put in center of bologna.
Cook in microwave until it curls in the shape of a bowl.
Apply ketchup as needed.
Makes one serving.

title: beef patties with onions
directions: Saute onions in margarine until golden.
Add salt, pepper and sugar; cook until onions are tender.
Remove and set aside.

title: mexican combo dip
directions: Mash avocados and mix next 3 ingredients with avocados.
Mix sour cream, mayo and taco mix together.
Layer bean dip, then avocado mash and on top of that sour cream mix; top with onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup butter in bowl and mix well. Spread and pat into bottom of 11x7 inch baking dish. Combine sugar and remaining butter in large bowl. Beat until light. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add a teaspoon vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy. Spread carefully over crumbs. Arrange bananas over mixture. Top with pineapple. Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts and garnish with cherry halves. Chill 2 hours.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Prepare jelly roll pan by greasing pan, inserting waxed paper and then greasing paper.
Beat eggs and sugar for 5 minutes.
Add pumpkin, flour, cinnamon and baking soda.
Pour pumpkin mixture into pan, sprinkle with nuts and bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Turn onto towel lightly coated with powdered sugar. Remove wax paper.
Roll up cake with towel and let cool.
Prepare filling by combining cream cheese, 1 c. powdered sugar, vanilla and butter. Beat until smooth.
Unroll cake and spread filling. Roll up (without towel) and refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with water and drain.
Mix in rest of ingredients and chill until sugar dissolves.

title: vickie's fried rice
directions: Have all ingredients ready in a large pot.
Add oil, garlic and beef that has been cut in small pieces.
Add sausage meat and carrots.
Cook until all meat is done.
Add both onions and mushrooms at this time.
Cook 1 minute.
Add bean sprouts, cook 1/2 minute.
Make a well in the middle of the mixture.
Add eggs. When eggs start to bead, add shrimp.
When the shrimp starts to turn pink, add the rice and keep stirring until completely mixed. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: taco chicken drummettes
directions: Cut chicken wings in half at joint; set aside. Combine drummettes and taco sauce in a shallow container. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. Combine bread crumbs and seasoning mix. Dredge drummettes in mixture and place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 16 drummettes.

title: cheesy o'brien egg scramble
directions: Prepare hash browns according to package directions. Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper. Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with soup. Set aside 1/2 cup of bacon; sprinkle remaining bacon over soup. Scramble eggs in a skillet in butter until nearly set. Spoon over bacon. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until done; reserve broth.
Pick all the meat off of the bones.
Butter a large baking dish.
Layer chicken in dish; spoon the can of soup over the chicken.
Add the package of stuffing (you can also use 1/2 package cornbread and 1/2 package herb), sprinkling over the soup.
Pour the chicken broth on top until you can see it around the edge.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Fix spaghetti by directions and rinse with cold water.
Mix all ingredients together and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat in finger size pieces; brown slowly in hot fat for about 15 minutes.
Add onion and garlic the last few minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; add to meat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
This may be done early in day and refrigerated.

Add tomatoes and bell pepper to meat mixture; cook 10 minutes longer. Combine cornstarch, water and soy sauce; stir into meat mixture. Bring to boil; cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes longer. Remove garlic and serve over hot noodles.
Serves 4.

title: icebox cheese wafers
directions: Cream together cheese, margarine, salt and pepper.
Add flour and make into a roll (1-inch).
Wrap in wax paper; place in refrigerator.
When needed, slice into thin wafers.
Place a pecan half on each wafer.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until tender.
In large bowl, combine thawed broccoli, rice, soup, water, cheese, milk and mushrooms.	Add onions.
Mix and pour into a 1-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or heated through.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: cheese-potato soup
directions: Place veggies in a 2-quart saucepan.
Barely cover with water. Simmer gently until tender.
Add milk.
Heat until warm.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Ready to serve.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Add enough water to make frying easy.
Shape into desired size patties.
Fry in oil until lightly browned on both sides.

title: upside-down fruit basket
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.

title: baked beans with hamburgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Add other ingredients. Bake in casserole for 1/2 hour or until brown at 350°.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter.
Line with graham cracker crumbs.
Cover completely with chocolate chips. Top with pecans, then layer with coconut.
Pour on condensed milk. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Let cool.
Cut into small squares.

title: super carrot-raisin salad
directions: Peel carrots and grate coarsely.
Add raisins and mix.
Blend together mayonnaise, honey and vinegar, then add cinnamon and mix thoroughly.
Pour over carrots and toss.
Let marinate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet and refrigerate until thick.
Add orange pieces (drained).
Allow to set and unmold to serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon, apples and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream.

title: onions
directions: Drain onions.
Heat margarine in skillet.
Add onions, sprinkle with sugar and cook slowly, turning the onions until they are golden brown.

title: beef fillets with mushrooms
directions: Sprinkle fillets with salt and pepper.
In large skillet, heat butter and brown fillets on both sides.
Push meat to one side of skillet; add onion.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Spoon onion over fillets.
Pour mushrooms on top; cover and simmer 25 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook sugars, corn syrup and water over medium heat, stirring frequently, until it reaches 290°.
Add the salt and continue cooking at a steady, low boil until it reaches 300°.
Remove from heat and stir in the butter, baking soda and vanilla.
Pour slowly over 7 to 8 quarts of popped corn, stirring until the kernels are well coated.
Keep the popped corn warm in the oven while the syrup is cooking.
Turn mixed caramel sauce and popped corn onto a clean, cool surface to cool.
Break into pieces and store in airtight containers.
Freezes well in airtight containers.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove and chop stems of mushrooms. Melt 2 Tbsp. of butter in frying pan over medium heat. Add mushroom stems and onion and cook, stirring until onions are limp. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice, crab, bread crumbs, egg, dill weed, and 1/4 c. of cheese. Mix well. Melt remaining 3 Tbsp. butter in 9x13 baking pan. Coat mushrooms in butter and turn cavity side up. Mound filling in each mushroom.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Pour wine in pan. Bake at 400° 15-20 minutes.

title: tarragon-dijon dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Excellent if watching your cholesterol or fat intake.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: company breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and brown in skillet.
Drain off grease and set aside.
Tear bread into small pieces and place in bottom of a 10 x 14-inch glass casserole dish which has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over bread.
Spread cheese over the meat.
Mix eggs with milk. Pour mixture over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar and 3 cups water. Boil hard for 20 minutes to make syrup.
Dissolve coffee in 1 cup boiling water.
Split vanilla bean lengthwise.
Drop in a 1/2 gallon jug.
Add vodka, syrup and coffee.
Let stand for 2 weeks and remove vanilla bean.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except beans, chips and dressing.
Add these when you are getting ready to eat.

title: annie's strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add berries and stir gently.
Chill until slightly congealed.
Add pineapple and nuts. Pour half into oiled 9-inch square dish and chill.
Fold sour cream into remainder, then pour on top of the partially set gelatin.
Chill until firm.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar, and pineapple.
Do not drain.
Cook in double boiler until thick, add margarine.
Cool.
Cut apples up (peeled) in small pieces.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Put in bowl and cover with Cool-Whip.
Roast the chopped nuts in oven about 5 minutes, and sprinkle chopped nuts on Cool-Whip.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Keeps several days.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook 8 slices bacon until crisp.
Remove and pour off half of the fat.
In remaining fat, cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Add tomatoes, water, long grain rice, chili sauce, salt, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and dash of pepper.
Cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top. Trim with parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into 1 pie crust.
Put butter on top of apples.
Top with second pie crust.
Slit the top so steam can escape.
Bake at 350° until top is brown and apples are cooked.

title: no egg cream pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in milk.
Cook over low heat until thick.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Blend together buttermilk and soda in large saucepan.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup, dash of salt and margarine.
Bring to a boil and cook to 240° to ball stage.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat; cool to lukewarm and add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Add sugar and milk.
Cook to soft ball stage for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add 1 cup peanut butter, 1 cup marshmallows and vanilla. Blend fast and pour in 8-inch pan quickly.
Wait until hardens.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate until easy to handle.
Roll into ball, then roll ball into nuts.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread rice (use the whole package plus the seasoning) over pan.
Put chicken pieces on top of rice. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over this.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, milk and water and pour over chicken and rice. Cover and bake for 3 hours at 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine juices, sugar and mint leaves and chill thoroughly. Just before serving, add ginger ale, soda water and quartered strawberries. Pour over large cake of ice in punch bowl. Float slices of lemon and lime. Serves 35.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take out of oven and, while hot, punch holes with a fork.
Mix condensed milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake.
Cool.
When ready to serve, top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: doris' toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Add flour and vanilla and blend well.
Spread dough into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Add flour and stir in until thick.
Knead flour into dough until firm.
Roll out dough until thin, about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into strips 1/2-inch wide and 3 to 4 inches long.
Drop into boiling broth one at a time and boil for a few minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook together.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and fill skillet with water; simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch.
Simmer 5 to 6 minutes.

title: lemon curd
directions: Cream sugar and
butter.
Squeeze
the lemons and grate the rinds.
Add this along
with
the
beaten egg yolks to the creamed mixture.
Heat in a double boiler.	Stir with a wooden spoon until it thickens.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Crush crackers and chop pecans.
Beat egg whites until very stiff and dry.
Fold in sugar and baking powder, a small amount at a time.
Fold in crackers, then pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a well-greased pie pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: authentic scotch shortbread cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients until well blended.

title: eggplant roll-ups
directions: Dip eggplant slices in eggs, then in bread crumbs, seasoned with garlic.
Brown lightly.
Lay on platter.
Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and parsley.

title: cheese onion loaf
directions: Mix and cook until onion is tender. Slice loaf of bread, side to side, not all the way through.
Brush mix into sliced bread. Add grated cheese between slices.
Double wrap in foil. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Brown under broiler.

title: shortening bread cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and knead with hands until smooth. Pinch off small pieces and make into rolls by rolling between palms.
Bake in moderate oven then roll in powdered sugar while still slightly warm.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
Saute onion and celery in a good shake of garlic salt and 1 teaspoon margarine.
Combine all ingredients in a large soup pot and simmer for several hours.

title: baked potato spears
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into wedges.
Brush with salad dressing.
Season with onion salt and pepper.
Place on greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Serves 4.

title: ham and shrimp jambalaya
directions: About 1 hour before serving, fry bacon until crisp; crumble for topping and set aside.
In bacon drippings, cook rice, onion, pepper and garlic until rice is lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, chicken broth, salt, bay leaf and thyme.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in ham, shrimp and hot sauce; cover and cook about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Sprinkle bacon crumbles over top before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: meal in one dish steak casserole
directions: Place steak in a long casserole; add salt and pepper.
Dot top of steak with butter and add Worcestershire sauce.
Then add potatoes, sliced in large pieces, onions, carrots ( whole or sliced) and the bell pepper.
Cover casserole with heavy foil. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove foil and cook 15 minutes longer, until browned.

title: marbled orange fudge
directions: Grease a 13x9x2-inch pan with 1 1/2 teaspoons butter. In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cream and remaining butter. Cook and stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil, stir for 4 minutes. Remove from heat, stir in the chips and marshmallow cream until smooth. Remove 1 cup and set aside. Add orange extract and food colorings to remaining mixture, stir until blended. Pour into prepared pan. Drop the reserved marshmallow mixture by tablespoonfuls over top. Cut through mixture with a knife to swirl. Cover and refrigerate until set. Cut into squares. Yield: about 2 1/2 pounds.

title: pasta with shrimp & feta cheese
directions: Cook pasta, drain well, and keep warm.
Saute shrimp in butter (oil) until pink, cooked through.
Add scallions, half of the chives and parsley.
Stir in feta cheese and season with pepper.
Place pasta in a serving bowl and top with shrimp/feta sauce.
Garnish with remaining chives.
Serves 4.

title: tortellini pasta salad with sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Combine marinade reserved from tomatoes (use entire bottle), oil, lemon juice and garlic in large bowl.
Stir in tomatoes, artichoke hearts and cashews.
Add tortellini and toss thoroughly. Season with salt and pepper.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cover and refrigerate.
Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Bring to room temperature prior to serving.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: sour dogs(microwave)
directions: Place wieners in buns and wrap each in paper towel.
Microwave for 3 minutes.

title: quincy juice
directions: Boil quince in water to cover. Strain out seeds, skin and stems. Mash remaining fruit. Add sugar to mashed fruit. Add quince mixture to juice and thin as desired with water. Adds a sparkly taste to orange and apple juices.

title: lattice top ice cream pie
directions: For crust: Combine cookie crumbs and butter until well blended.
Press onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool and chill.

title: one of david's favorites
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add chilies.
Drain well and add soup and milk.
Break tortillas up and just poke them in the meat.
I add pinto beans sometimes and it makes it go farther.
Add cheese and let it melt.
My kids love this!
It's really good.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil the sugar, oleo, cocoa, milk and salt two minutes. Remove from fire.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.
Enjoy.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Add
English
peas, soup and Cheddar cheese to a casserole dish
and
mix
well.
Melt
the butter and pour over the crushed crackers.
Spread
this
over the top and bake in 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and oil.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in butterscotch pudding and butterscotch chips and pecans.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: viele good quiche
directions: Place cheese, ham, bacon and vegetables in bottom of 2 deep dish pie crusts.
Whip eggs.
Add milk to eggs, then pour 1/2 of mixture over each pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour, until quiche is formed.
Frozen pie shells work well.

title: c. m. p. dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool completely.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir syrup, eggs and sugar; add flour.
Add melted butter and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oregon walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add syrup, sugar, salt, vanilla and butter. Add walnuts.
Pour
into
unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding well.
Add remaining ingredients. Keep refrigerated.

title: five decker dinner
directions: Cut bacon into pieces and line the bottom of a Dutch oven. Shape ground beef into patties and place over bacon.
Sprinkle with celery salt, salt and pepper.
Cover patties with onions, potatoes and carrots.
Season.
Place parsley on top and cook five minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water, cover and cook over low heat 35 to 45 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine the egg yolks, lime juice and condensed milk.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue made from the 4 egg whites.

title: vena's italian chicken
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken pieces.
Rub each piece of chicken with vegetable oil.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with nonstick shortening.
Sprinkle both sides of chicken with salt, garlic powder and rosemary.
Keep chicken, skin side up.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
When chicken is almost done, remove cover and bake until crisp and golden brown.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Cook eggplant until tender in 1/2 cup water.
Add milk to moisten cracker crumbs.
Add soup and eggplant.
Add egg, salt and pepper.
Mix together; put in a greased casserole.
Dot thickly with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° until done and lightly browned.

title: chocolate chip crunchies
directions: In a large saucepan melt chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat.
(Be careful not to burn.)
Remove from heat and stir in the cornflakes with a wooden spoon.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: self filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to directions on package.
Fill paper baking cups 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar and salt; beat in the egg.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful of mixture in each cupcake.
Bake according to cake directions.
Makes 30 cupcakes.

title: pasta with sugar, snap peas, asparagus and parmesan
directions: Add asparagus to large pot of boiling salted water.
Cook until just crisp-tender.
Transfer to bowl of cold water using slotted spoon.
Cool slightly and drain.
Add pasta to same pot of water and boil until tender, but still firm to bite.
Add peas and boil 2 minutes.
Add asparagus and heat through.
Drain well.
Return pasta-vegetable mixture to pot.
Add oil and toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup cheese.
Serve immediately. Serves 4.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole, stir together peanuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stir well.
Cook 4 more minutes on High.
Stir in butter or margarine and vanilla.
Microwave 2 minutes longer on High.
Add baking soda and stir quickly until light and foamy.
Immediately pour on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Let cool 1 hour.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, cup of flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine eggs, 2 cups sugar, lemon juice, lemon rind, baking powder, 4 tablespoons flour and a dash of salt in crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Dust liberally with confectioners sugar.

title: brown rice
directions: Dice onion and hot dogs; place in baking dish with margarine. Put in oven at 350° until sauteed, then pour beef consomme, a cup of water and rice into this mixture.
Bake at 350° until rice is tender (about 30 minutes) in a covered baking dish.

title: tuna pate
directions: Drain
tuna
well.
Cream everything else together real well. Then
mix
tuna slowly.
Cover thinly with Miracle Whip and sprinkle with parsley.

title: fricadill (danish meat balls)
directions: Mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Brown on all sides and cook gently for 25 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix together well flour, Crisco, sugar and salt.
Add egg, vinegar and cold water and cut with fork to mix.
Cool 1/2 hour.

title: scandinavian vegetable and cheese salad
directions: The cheese salad, known as Salata Horiatiki, appears with wide variation throughout Greece.

title: pineapple casserole #2
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup juice.
Combine pineapple and juice with sugar, flour and eggs.
Place into a 2-quart baking dish. Top with bread cubes.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 to 50 minutes or until set and light brown. Good as a side dish with ham or chicken.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Soak dried lima beans in water overnight.
Cook beans until soft.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on top of range until hot.

title: korean bul-go-ki
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Mix all ingredients together in bowl with meat.
Marinate 2 hours or more.
Quick-fry in wok or skillet.

title: mai tai punch
directions: In 4 quart nonmetal container, combine all ingredients. Refrigerate.
Serve over ice.
Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: cheese dreams
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on hamburger roll halves.
Toast under broiler until golden.

title: peanut mallows
directions: Heat chocolate chips, condensed milk and margarine in saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth; remove from heat. Stir in peanuts and mallows.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: date loaf(excellent at christmas - makes great gifts)
directions: Coat dates with small amount flour; add nuts.
Mix well.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream egg yolks with sugar.
In small bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; fold into sugar and egg mixture in large bowl and mix well.
Use electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Batter should be fluffy.

Sift flour, salt and baking powder together in appropriate size bowl, then add flour mixture into egg and sugar mixture, mixing well by folding in a little at a time, making sure flour is well absorbed.
Use beater after folding in, if needed.

Next, add nuts and date mixture into batter, adding a little at a time until mixture is well blended. Pour into well-greased, floured baking pan large enough so that batter is 1/2-inch thick in bottom.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut in squares.
May coat with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well and set overnight.
Keep refrigerated and covered.
Will keep for 6 weeks.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Do this in oven while it's preheating.
Remove from oven when margarine begins to brown.
Mix dry ingredients and milk; pour onto melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Peel peaches; slice and place on top of dough mixture.
Again, do not stir.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oatmeal caramelitas
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, oats, brown sugar, soda, salt and melted butter.
Take half of this mixture and press into a 9-inch square pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
After the crust has been baked, sprinkle the following on the crust:
chocolate chips and pecans.
Mix caramel topping with 3 tablespoons flour and drizzle over the chocolate chips and nuts.
Sprinkle the remaining crumbs over the caramel topping and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: chicken on a jar
directions: You will also need 1 heat resistant jar.

title: plain roll dough
directions: Soften compressed yeast in lukewarm water (85°).
Active dry yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm and add softened yeast and egg.
Gradually stir in flour to form soft dough.
Beat vigorously.
Cover and let rise in warm place (82°) until double in bulk about 2 hours.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and proceed as desired under variation.

title: corn and mac bake
directions: In a greased baking dish, put cream style corn and whole kernel corn, undrained.
Add melted margarine and 1 cup cubed Cheddar cheese.
Add 1 cup of cooked macaroni.
Mix and bake at 350° until it is bubbly and set. (No salt needed in this recipe as the cheese provides enough salt.)

title: traveling cupcakes
directions: Melt cocoa and margarine; stir in nuts.
Beat eggs with a fork.
Add sugar, flour, vanilla and salt.
Add chocolate and margarine mixture.
Stir well.
Spoon into muffin tins with paper liners.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 24 and will stack and travel well without crushing.

title: sandies
directions: Cream together first 2 ingredients.
Add next 2 ingredients; mix well.
Add the flour and mix well, then add the nuts.
Form into small rolls 1 1/2-inches long.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in slow oven (300°) for 20 minutes or until delicately brown. While hot, roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: ice cream cheesecake
directions: Combine cream cheese and ice cream.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Top with fresh berries.

title: buffalo bills' taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream (blender or mixer).
Spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Brown meat.
Drain.
Add taco seasoning and 1 cup water.
Bring to boil, then simmer 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread cooled meat mixture over cream cheese and sour cream.
Layer diced tomato and onion.
Spread picante sauce over.
Cover all with cut lettuce.
Top with shredded Cheddar. Sprinkle with sliced olives.
Serve chilled with tortilla chips.

title: mint tea
directions: Boil water.
Add tea bags 10 minutes.
Pour into pitcher.
Add sugar, orange and lemon juice.
Serve over ice cubes.

title: bambini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cheeses.
Cut each biscuit in half, making 40 thin pieces.
Gently shape each biscuit into a 2 1/2 x 4-inch oval.
Place slice of pepperoni on dough.
Top with scant tablespoon of cheese mixture.
Moisten edge and fold over to enclose filling; pinch edges to seal.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: seventh heaven
directions: Divide cake cubes and fruit among 6 dessert glasses.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl until completely dissolved.
Mix cold water or cranberry cocktail and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring, until slightly thickened.
Remove any remaining ice.

title: louisiana pepper pecans
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir in pecans.
Let stand 30 minutes; drain.
Spread pecans evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Great as a Christmas gift!

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain juices from fruits. Combine and add enough water to make 5 cups. Heat juices. Dissolve jello in juices and pour heated mixture over frozen orange juice and fruits. Mix and refrigerate.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add miniature marshmallows and sour cream.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add crushed pineapple with juice and chopped nuts.
Let stand until almost firm.
Fold in whipped whipping cream.
Refrigerate.

title: creamy fruit mix
directions: Drain oranges; mix with other fruit along with syrup.
Add instant pudding and mix well.
Will thicken as it sets.
May add bananas or grapes for slightly different taste.

title: mama's chow chow
directions: Grind peppers and onions in blender.
Put in large pot and add sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and cook over medium heat for 25 minutes.
Put in pint jars and seal.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix and cook first four ingredients 2 minutes.
Take off and stir in peanut butter and oats.
Stir until thick enough to drop on wax paper.

title: appetizer for summer picnic
directions: Dice vegetables.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Add 2 slices cubed bread (no crust).
Let stand overnight.
Serve in small cups to drink.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix the ingredients, then add vegetables and mix.
Marinate overnight.

title: spanish lasagna
directions: Layer the chicken, sour cream, cream cheese, salsa and Cheddar cheese between the tortillas.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Layer in a deep-round bowl.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Simmer 1 cup berries in 2/3 cup water for 3 minutes.
Drain and save juice.
Mix sugar and cornstarch in 1/3 cup water; add to strawberry juice.
Bring to boil; stir and boil until thick.
Add salt and red food coloring.
Place sliced berries in baked pie shell (crust.).
Pour glaze over and chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chicken caesar salad
directions: Heat oil in nonstick skillet over medium-high heat.
Toss chicken with lemon and pepper seasoning and garlic powder to evenly coat.
Add to skillet and cook 4 to 5 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Do not drain off oil.

title: fresh apple cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cloves, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon and set aside.
Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and milk. Beat until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture.
Add apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with xxx sugar frosting.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add prunes, buttermilk, vanilla and nuts. Mix well.
Pour into well-greased large pan and bake at 350° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Good with whipped cream or glaze.

title: turkey piccata
directions: Place turkey between 2 sheets of wax paper; pound to 1/8 inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place flour on plate.
Dip turkey in flour to coat both sides, shaking off excess.

title: mommy's best lemon stickies
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine, and 1 egg and mix well.
Press into greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Mix well the cream cheese, 2 eggs, and confectioners sugar.
Spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put
broken up (or
rolled
into
balls)
hamburger
in bottom of 9 x
9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and green pepper and pour
soup over top.
Place Tater Tots on top. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork and bean pudding
directions: Place 4 slices of bacon in greased pie plate.
Cover with pork and beans; spoon tomatoes over beans.
Sprinkle with 2 Tbsp. sugar.
Place 4 slices of bacon on tomatoes.
Cover with bread crumbs, dot with margarine and sprinkle with 2 Tbsp. sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add beef.
Cook, stirring to break apart, until light brown.
Drain oil.
Add all other ingredients and cook slowly for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: colorful casserole
directions: Combine tomatoes, corn, green pepper and onion in a casserole and mix well.
Combine margarine, bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
Put into 2-quart casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine 1 can cream of chicken soup with mayonnaise.
Mix with broccoli and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Top with bread crumbs and sprinkle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook butter, milk and flour until thick.
Add cheese, pimento, mushrooms, tuna, eggs and cooked noodles.
Mix well and put in casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: black bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight. Drain beans. Discard water. In a 4-quart saucepan, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add the next 6 ingredients. Cook until onion is tender. Add the beans, 6 cups water and bay leaf. Bring to boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Cool slightly.
Remove bay leaf. Place about 1 cup in blender; blend on high about 1 minute or until smooth. Repeat with second cup. Return all to saucepan. Cook chorizo and drain well.
Add to beans. Add the lime juice; cook about 20 minutes. If desired, serve with a dollop of sour cream on each serving.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into ice cream freezer container and finish filling with milk.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons of ice cream.
Fruit may be added, if desired.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar to eliminate stickiness.
Put on wax-papered cookie sheet and leave at room temperature overnight; this dries them out a little, slightly crusting them.

title: mulligan stew
directions: Using a stewpot, mix separated corned beef with all of the other ingredients.
Season to your own taste.
May vary by adding other vegetables.
Let simmer at least 1 hour.
Serve when hot. Easy to heat up.

title: "slivered green beans"
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat, then add slivered almonds.
Heat until the almonds turn color (darker) and begin to soften.
Be sure not to burn.
Then drain almonds and add can of beans and heat as usual.

title: holiday punch
directions: Heat the cider in a large pan.
Add the water and orange juice.
After the mixture starts to steam, add vanilla and cinnamon.

title: pork chop and baked beans casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pork chops) and pour into casserole dish.
Lay pork chops on top and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Turn chops and bake 45 minutes or until chops are brown. Beans give pork chops barbecue flavor.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel onions and slice thinly.
Cook slowly in butter in a large covered pot, until tender and golden.
Stir frequently.
Add broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes. Put in individual ovenproof bowls.
Place a slice of French bread on top; sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler until brown (about 5 minutes).

title: apple raisin pie
directions: Take a pastry for a double-crust pie (pastry dough) and divide in half.
Roll half of the dough on a lightly floured surface into a 12-inch circle.
Wrap the pastry around a rolling pin.
Unroll on a 9-inch pie plate, being careful not to stretch the pastry. Trim to 1/2-inch beyond the edge of the pie plate.
Roll the remaining pastry to a 14-inch wide strip; set aside.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans in water overnight; drain.
Saute onions, garlic and pork or ham until onions are transparent.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for about 4 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: maple candy
directions: Line a 13 x 9 x 2 in baking pan with foil, buttered. Set aside. Combine syrup, cream and butter in large saucepan. Bring to boil. Cook 9 minutes after it starts to boil. Remove from heat, add nuts and extract. Stir with wooden spoon for 4 minutes in pan.

title: how to preserve a husband
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Don't choose too young.
When selected give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist on keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them hard and sometimes bitter.
Some choose to make them sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
Serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in large pot or dutch oven. Cover with water to 2 inches above beans. Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 1 hour. Drain. Cook bacon until crisp; crumble and set aside. Add bell pepper and next 8 ingredients to drippings in bacon pan; saute 10 minutes or until browned. Stir in broth, scraping pan to loosen bacon bits. Add beans. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until beans are tender. Serve in bowl, topped with crumbled bacon and parsley.

title: pumpkin white chip macadamia bars
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, cloves and baking soda in small bowl. Beat butter and sugars in large mixer bowl until creamy. Beat in pumpkin, egg and vanilla until blended. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in 1 1/2 cups morsels and nuts. Spread into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 18 to 22 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Boil chicken with celery stalk, carrot and clove studded onion until tender, 30 to 60 minutes.

title: atlanta banana bread(flavor improves with time)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
In separate bowl mix baking soda and sour cream.
To sugar, butter and egg mixture add flour, bananas, vanilla and salt.
Fold in baking soda and sour cream mixture and fold in walnuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead.
Freezes well.
Yields:
1 loaf.

title: turkey barbecue on buns
directions: Pan fry celery, onion and green pepper in butter until lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients except buns and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Spoon half of mixture into a 1 pint freezer container.
Cool, label and freeze for a future meal (3 cups).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Coat pan with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Cube bread and place in pan.
Crumble sausage and brown; drain and place on top of bread.
Beat the eggs and add milk and salt.
Pour over sausage. Top with cheese and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sunny banana shake
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend on high for 1 minute or until drink is smooth.
Serve with a sprinkle of cinnamon, if desired.
Makes 2 six ounce servings.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and spices; set aside.
In a large bowl, use electric mixer at medium speed and gradually add 1 cup sugar to the shortening, creaming until light and fluffy.
Blend in molasses and eggs.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture until combined. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in remaining 1/3 cup sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown. Let cool 1 minute before removing to wire rack to cool.

title: green chili and corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook celery, onion, garlic, cumin and oregano or marjoram in hot oil until onion is tender but not brown.
Stir in chicken broth, corn, red sweet pepper and green chili peppers.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine milk and flour; stir into corn mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese; cook and stir until cheese melts. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Fluff once with a fork.
If the mixture dries out or if you want to reheat it, add a little water.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer 5 minutes.
Press uncooked rolls into bottom and sides of an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan, pressing edges together to seal.

title: "better than robert redford" dessert
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, mix and mash flour, margarine, 1/2 cup nuts and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool. Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Spread on top of cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk; spread on cream cheese layer.
Spread with Cool Whip and top with nuts.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Tastes best when prepared a few hours before serving.

title: fresh refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in 1/16-inch pieces. Combine with pepper and onion in bowl. Sprinkle with salt and celery seed. Let stand 1 hour. Combine sugar and white vinegar; stir to blend. Pour over pickles and stir. Cover and refrigerate. Ready to eat in a day.

title: southern comfort punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve.

title: pear crunch
directions: Mix pear slices with brown sugar in baking dish.
Set aside. Mix flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon and set aside.
Beat egg; mix with flour mixture.
Spread over fruit.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve warm.
Makes about 6 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: pistachio cheesecake
directions: Combine flour and almonds; cut in butter until crumbly. Press onto sides and bottom of a greased 10-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: our favorite meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, saute bacon over medium heat until partially cooked.
In large bowl, beat eggs with salt, pepper, thyme, nutmeg and cloves until well mixed.
Stir in milk, sour cream and bread crumbs.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add beef, pork, veal, onion, chopped parsley, celery leaves, chives and garlic.
Mix lightly until well blended.

title: leah's garlic potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in quarters. Boil potatoes until soft, about 30 minutes. Drain potatoes and put back into pot with lid. Add butter, garlic salt and pepper. Put lid on and shake, firmly coating potatoes.

title: hot chocolate drink
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add 4 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.
Very good for parties.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add egg yolks one at a time, beating after each one.
Dissolve soda in sour cream and add alternately with flour.
Begin and end with flour.
Add flavorings and fold in stiff beaten egg whites.
Pour in a tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
(This recipe is over 100 years old.
Keeps well.)

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef in butter in large skillet; breaking up meat with a fork. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Simmer for 1 hour. Serve on buns.

title: tex-mex skillet chicken
directions: Toss chicken with cumin and salt; set aside.
Cook onion, green pepper and garlic in oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add chicken; cook and stir until chicken is no longer pink, about 3 minutes.
Add picante sauce, rice and broth; mix well.
Bring to a boil and cover.
Remove from heat; let stand until all liquid is absorbed, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let set 1 minute.
Sprinkle with tomato and olives.
Serve with additional picante sauce.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour beans into saucepan on stove.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Cook at medium to low temperature until hot (or bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes; you may top with bacon strips when baking before putting in oven if you like).

title: carter eggs
directions: Place 1 tablespoon of cooking oil in skillet.
Place skillet on stove eye on medium heat.
Beat two eggs well.
Add dash of salt and 2 tablespoons milk.
Add 1/4 cup shredded sharp Cheddar cheese.
Pour in hot skillet.
Do not stir until eggs puff up and appear to be done on bottom side.
Less stirring makes better eggs.
Serve with homemade biscuits only.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and 10x powdered sugar.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: special potato soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Combine with next ingredients to milk.
Remove from heat and mash with potato masher.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Makes approximately 8 cups.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in covered bowl in refrigerator until ready to use.
Bake at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce raisin bread
directions: Blend shortening (oleo), sugar and eggs.
Add raisins, applesauce and nuts.
Sift together flour, salt and spices.
Add in several portions to first mixture.
Before last flour is added, dissolve soda in hot water.
Add to mixture; beat in remaining flour.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fettuccine ala romano
directions: Bring 8 quarts of water to a boil; add salt and very gently drop in noodles.
Cook until done, but do not overcook.
Drain in colander.
Put in heated serving bowl.
Add the creamed butter and cheese together.
Toss very gently.
Season generously.
Add egg yolk and cream, beating constantly.
Beat in the grated cheese and butter and put over noodles a few tablespoons at a time.
Serve immediately.

title: grandma green's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Stir in oats, pecans and dates.
Roll into rolls and refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and cook at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: potato and leek soup with crispy bacon
directions: Chop potatoes into 1 cm cubes.
Cut bacon into thin strips. Heat half the oil in pan; add bacon and cook, stirring, until bacon is crisp.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Heat remaining oil in pan; add leek and garlic and cook, stirring, until leek is soft. Stir in stock and half the potatoes; simmer, covered, until potatoes are tender.
Blend or process potato mixture until smooth; return to pan with remaining potato and half the bacon. Simmer, uncovered, until potato is tender.
Stir in cream, milk, chives and mustard; stir until heated through.
Serve soup sprinkled with remaining bacon.
Serves 2.
Soup can be made a day ahead.
Storage:
Covered, in refrigerator.
Freeze:
Not suitable.
Microwave:
Suitable.

title: 7 layered salad
directions: Break up in pieces and layer 1-inch deep lettuce; layer next 5 ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise, salt and garlic powder.
Spread on top of salad.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight. Before serving, add grated cheese and bacon bits.
Serve.

title: cheese snacks
directions: Cream oleo, flour, cheese and pepper.
Add Rice Krispies and stir with a spoon.
Make small balls and press with a fork on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until brown at 325°.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until cooked.

Test with a fork for doneness. Cut in half and scoop out while hot and mix with cooked whipped potatoes. Add margarine, cheese, seasoning, cream and bacon. Fill empty potato shells with mixture and wrap in Saran Wrap. Freeze until ready to use.
Make ahead of time so you can enjoy your party along with your guests.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir only until the flour is moist.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti on toast
directions: Cook spaghetti along with onions until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add can of tomato soup and rinse with 1/2 can of water. Add 1 tablespoon of cooking oil.
Cook approximately 10 minutes. You may add 1 small can of tomato juice if the mixture is too thick.
Serve on buttered toast.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring cocoa, margarine and water to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add sugar and flour, mix well.
Add soda, buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Bake 15 - 20 minutes at 350.
Pour into 11 X 16 inch pan.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: To prepare meat, put salt, pepper and garlic salt on meat and let stand overnight.

title: taco pie casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and water. Simmer for 5 minutes.
Separate rolls and place in a 10-inch pie pan, pressing and cutting to form crust.
Sprinkle 1 cup Doritos on bottom of crust.
Put meat mixture over Doritos; spread sour cream over meat mixture and cover with cheese.
Add remaining Doritos.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: grammaw's cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together. Stir in some half and half until dissolved.
Put remaining half and half, cream and butter on medium heat and let come to almost boil.
Add sugar mixture and when it starts to thicken, pour into unbaked pie shells. Sprinkle with a little nutmeg and then drizzle 2 teaspoons vanilla on top and bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup salted water.
When tender, add soup, cheese and milk.
Do not boil, just heat.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar, salt, butter and evaporated milk for 6 minutes. Put in large bowl the chocolate bits, German chocolate, Marshmallow Fluff and nuts.
Pour boiling mixture over ingredients in bowl.
Beat until chocolate is all melted and pour in greased pan (1 large pan or 2 small pans).
Let stand in refrigerator several hours.
Cut and store in tight can.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes well and dry thoroughly.
Bake in microwave or at 325° until you can pierce with fork.
Cut baked potatoes lengthwise.
Scoop out potato and mix with butter, sour cream, cheese, salt, pepper, onions and crab meat.
Refill potato shells. Sprinkle with paprika.
At this point, potatoes can be wrapped and frozen for future use.
To serve immediately, reheat in very hot oven for 15 minutes.

title: german lebkuchen
directions: The day before baking, cut up dates and cover with juice and rinds of orange and lemon.
Mix well and let stand overnight (covered and in refrigerator).
Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Sift flour with cinnamon, baking powder and coffee. Add alternately with date mixture and nuts.
Spread thin in long pans (16 x 10-inch).
Takes all batter.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375°.
When cool, cut in thin strips.
Ice, if desired.
Use confectioners sugar icing made with melted butter (margarine) and orange juice.
Makes 4 dozen pieces.

title: cowboy-vegetable soup
directions: Put in crock-pot; mix all together!
Makes delicious soup to serve with cornbread.
Cook on high for 1/2 day or on low all day. Enjoy!

title: pecan brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and set aside.
Combine sugar, water and syrup in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until a small amount of syrup forms a soft ball in very cold water.
Add butter and pecans.
Cook, stirring constantly until a small amount of mix dropped into cold water separates into threads which are very hard and brittle (do not burn).
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda mixture; mix thoroughly. Pour on 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Let cool.

title: kelly's 7-layer cookie
directions: Melt butter in pan, press down graham crackers and butter. Top with coconut all over.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: grandma's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats; set aside.
Sift salt, cinnamon, soda and flour together.
Cream butter, sugars and eggs.
Mix in oat mixture and flour mixture alternating until well mixed; then add nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: In top double boiler, melt chocolate over hot water.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetened condensed milk, vanilla, salt and, if desired, nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Turn into wax paper lined 8-inch pan.
Chill.
Store in airtight container.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 5-quart saucepan.
Cook on medium-low heat for 2 hours.

title: rice krispie balls
directions: Chop dates and pecans.
Melt butter in saucepan; add sugar and dates and simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cereal and nuts.
Cool until soft ball can be formed.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Store in covered container.
Easy to make and very, very good.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Add apples and mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: golden ham casserole
directions: Brown ham and onion in butter.
Arrange layers of ham and vegetables in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Make cream sauce of remaining butter, flour and milk.
Add salt and cheese. Cook over low heat until slightly thickened.
Pour over ham and vegetable layers.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pennsylvania dutch spinach
directions: Fry bacon crisp and add to spinach.
Add flour to drippings and blend.
Add hot water and cook until thick.
Add sugar, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour over spinach.
Stir until wilted.
Garnish with eggs.
Serves 6.

title: de sarno spaghetti
directions: Cover bottom of large skillet with olive oil and saute onion and garlic until golden.
Add meats and cook until brown.
Add all other ingredients except pasta and simmer on lowest setting at least 1/2 hour (the longer the better).
Cook noodles and mangia!

title: potato casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread potatoes and add 1 stick melted margarine.
Mix together sour cream, soup, salt and cheese. Spread over potatoes.
Place corn flakes on top and drizzle 1/2 stick melted margarine over them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered, then 10 to 15 minutes, uncovered.
When making a double batch, cook 20 minutes longer uncovered.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot yeast rolls
directions: Add yeast to water; stir until dissolved.
Add 2 cups flour. Mix well.
Let stand 25 minutes.
Knead well on floured surface. Pulling off small handfuls, work into balls (size of plum) and place into greased pan.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° until golden brown on top about the time the smell will drive you crazy and you can't wait to eat one!

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: You will need 1 plastic dipping fork and 1 package small fluted cups.

title: soft pretzels
directions: In large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, undissolved yeast and salt.
Heat milk, water and oil until very warm (120-130 degrees).
Stir into dry ingredients.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 4-6 minutes.
Cover; let rest 5-10 minutes until risen slightly.
To shape into pretzel by making a long rope sharp then curve ends of each rope to make a circle, cross ends at top. Twist ends once and lay over bottom of circle.
Place on 2 greased baking sheets.
Brush with a beaten eggs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, brush again with eggs and sprinkle with poppyseed, sesame seed, salt or cheese.
Return to oven and bake for 15 minutes more or until done.
Remove and let cool on wire racks.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken breasts.
Mix egg and water together.
Crush Ritz crackers with rolling pin.
Dip chicken in egg-water mixture and roll in crackers.
Arrange on baking sheet.
Combine maple syrup and butter.
Drizzle over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate in a glass, microwave-safe bowl in microwave until melted and smooth.

title: maypo muffins
directions: Bake 15 to 20 minutes in oven at 400°.
Makes 9 large muffins.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl; beat 3 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sangria (fruit punch)
directions: In a large pitcher, combine sugar, orange
juice and grape juice.
Add lemon, orange and apple or peach.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Just before serving, add club soda.
Put ice cubes into 8 glasses.
Pour Sangria over ice and spoon some fruit into each glass.

title: holiday mixed green salad
directions: Bring 1 cup orange juice to simmer in heavy small saucepan. Remove from heat. Mix in dried cranberries. Let stand until softened, about 30 minutes. Drain well. Discard soaking juice. Whisk oil, vinegar, orange peel and remaining 3 tablespoons juice in small bowl to blend. Mix in cranberries. Season dressing to taste with salt and pepper. Cover and refrigerate. Bring to room temperature before serving. Place greens in large bowl. Toss with 2/3 of dressing. Divide greens among 6 plates. Add orange segments and toss with remaining dressing. Top salads with orange segments and pecans.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: Mix all items together with a mixer.
Put a vanilla wafer in each cup liner in a muffin pan.
Add about 1 tablespoon of cheese filling on each vanilla wafer.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas stollen(yield:  9 to 11)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add 1/2 cup honey.
Sift together flour, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add 4 cups of dry ingredients to yeast mixture.
May mix with electric hand mixer on slow to medium speed.
Cover and let rise about 1/2 hour to light spongy consistency.

title: alfredo fettucine with yogurt
directions: Contains 300 calories and 5 grams of fat.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and sift together.
Add beaten eggs, Crisco, strawberries and pecans.
Stir just enough to moisten ingredients.
Spoon batter into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole with velveeta cheese
directions: Brown onions in butter; cut cheese in cubes and melt into butter.
Add soup and milk.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix in broccoli and rice with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat nachos
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add taco sauce, ketchup and salt and pepper.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with chips.
Cover chips with meat, then sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake in 325° oven for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients; melt slowly in heavy saucepan.
To avoid sticking, do not turn the burner up too high.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in 1-quart lightly salted water for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken to cool; save broth.
In bottom of a large (6 to 8-quart) casserole dish, place frozen vegetables and 1 1/2 cups of chicken broth.
Remove chicken from bone and place over vegetables.
Mix 1 cup chicken broth with 1 can chicken soup and pour over layer of chicken.
Mix salt and pepper, flour and melted margarine and spoon over casserole.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.

title: crunchy chocolate squares
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir until smooth.
Add cereal and peanuts and stir until well blended. Press into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 64 candies.

title: sausage, escarole and potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes, quarter and boil until tender.
Boil escarole. Cut mild sausage into 1-inch rings.
Put oil in a nonstick skillet and fry sausage with onion.
Drain and add escarole.
Drain and add potatoes.
Fry on low for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Delicious 1 pot meal.
Easy to serve.

title: tamale bites
directions: Mix cornbread and 1/2 cup enchilada sauce, salt and ground round.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° until done.
Mix remaining enchilada sauce and tomato sauce.
Put meat balls into baking dish and pour on the sauce.
Top with cheese.
Serve warm.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and margarine to boil.
Boil hard for 7 1/2 minutes.
Take off heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir and pour in buttered dish.

title: frosted fruit salad
directions: Dissolve lemon and orange jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add 1 1/2 cups water with juice of 1 lemon (optional).
Add pineapple, bananas and marshmallow bits.
Pour into long Pyrex dish and chill.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add cream, water, butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Add coconut.
Beat egg yolks.
Add to mixture.
Cook over medium heat in heavy saucepan.
Pour into cooked pie shell.
Save egg whites for meringue.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in order named.
Pour into casserole or loaf pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/4 hours. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut and quarter canned biscuits.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Shake half of quartered biscuits in mix and place in tubed nonstick pan.
Mix margarine, brown sugar and nuts, then pour over quarters in pan.
Then add remaining quarters in pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes (use own judgement).
Turn pan upside-down on plate and serve warm.
Good with coffee and/or orange juice.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together with a fork or pastry blender the butter, powdered sugar and flour.
Pat into an ungreased 9-inch square pan. Bake in a 375° oven for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Mix together the sugar, eggs, lemon juice, salt and lemon rind. Pour over crust.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes. Sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: friday spaghetti
directions: Brown onion, parsley, garlic and mushrooms in margarine.
Add tomato sauce, water and juice from mushrooms.
Add the sugar. Cook spaghetti according to package instructions.
Drain the spaghetti noodles.
Mix together.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Place in refrigerator to congeal.
Yields 24 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Mix 7-Up and punch.
Add sherbets; refrigerate.

title: punch
directions: Stir and freeze ahead of time if a slush is desired.

title: monkey bread buttery sweet dough
directions: Prepare dough as directed.
Grease 12-cup fluted ring pan; set aside.
Divide dough into 30 pieces with sharp knife.
In small bowl, mix granulated sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Stir in nuts.
Coat each piece of dough with melted butter, then with sugar mixture.
Layer in prepared pan.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: cheesy potato patties
directions: Prepare potatoes as directed on package for 4 servings, except decrease water to 1 cup.
Stir in cheese and onion.
Refrigerate until cool enough to handle, about 10 minutes.
Divide into 6 equal parts; shape each into patty.
Coat patties with dry potatoes.
Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet until melted.
