Cook patties over medium heat until golden brown, 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Makes 6 patties.

title: mustard pickles
directions: For 2 gallons of cucumbers, make brine of 2 cups salt to one gallon of water.
Let stand 1 week.
Skim each day if needed. Drain and cut in chunks.
For 3 days make a boiling hot solution of 1 quart water and 1 tablespoon powdered alum.
Pour off 3 mornings. Make a fresh solution each day.
Drain the fourth day.
Heat 6 cups vinegar, 5 cups sugar, 1/3 cup pickling spice and 1 tablespoon celery seed to boiling.
Pour over pickles.
Drain, heat and pour back over pickles 3 mornings.
Drain and save solution.
Add 2 cups sugar.
Heat and pour over pickles.
Drain the sixth morning.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Heat and pour over pickles packed in sterilized jars. Seal while hot.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix well in blender, store in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin rice pudding
directions: Cook rice. Set aside. In a large saucepan, bring milk, pumpkin, rice, sugar, cinnamon, ginger and salt to a boil. Simmer about 6 minutes.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook large pieces of cabbage in boiling salted water for 5 to 7 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Drain cabbage.
Cut off thick stems and cut into small pieces.
While cabbage is cooking, prepare the buttered crumbs and white sauce.
When last portion of milk is added to sauce, add the cheese.
When cheese is melted, layer cabbage and sauce in a greased baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles. Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 cheese mixture, 1/2 Mozzarella and 1/2 meat.
Repeat layering.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry custard pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs and butter.
Put on top of strawberries.
Put strawberries in unbaked pie shell.
Add custard and bake at 425° until strawberries are done.
Put meringue on top and brown.
Bake at 300° for meringue.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Shape into a loaf and bake about 1 hour, until browned.
Remove excess fat.
Let stand about 10 minutes for easier slicing.

title: mother's fruit cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter; add molasses and mix in the eggs one at a time.
Add the spices and stir well to get a uniform mixture.
Measure the flour and the baking powder into a paper bag; close the bag and shake well to mix properly.
Mix fruit and nuts in a very large bowl and flour the fruit and nuts with the flour in the bag.
Use a handful at a time and stir the mixture. I have found that nothing beats the hands at this stage of the mixing.
Continue adding the flour and mixing until all of the flour is on the fruit and nuts.

Now, mix the egg mixture with the fruit mixture; this takes time and strength and a very large bowl. Grease the baking pans with butter and line with waxed paper. You will have enough batter to make 3 good sized cakes and a spring-form pan would work very well for this.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.
I have found that because good currants are hard to find that for me it works best to increase the candied fruit and add 1 pound of pecans.
This cake will freeze very well and bourbon or rum poured over the cake before cutting or freezing does seem to help.

title: spicy zucchini
directions: Slice zucchini into about 1-inch slices.
Blend the tomato soup and 1/2 can water with the pepper and garlic.
Place the zucchini in a coverable glass microwave dish.
Add mixture and mix well.
Cover and microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese; mix well, cover and microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on zucchini; cover and microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and let stand covered for 5 minutes.
Serve with hot buttery garlic bread.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasoning.
Press firmly into a greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with mashed potatoes.
Top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zippity kielbasa pasta
directions: In frying pan, saute oil, rosemary, garlic, mushrooms and kielbasa until browned.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and half and half; stir.
Pour over boiled rigatoni.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add water.
Cook until it boils and is clear and thickened.
Remove from heat, let cool 10 minutes.
Add Jell-O.
Mix well.
Pour over strawberries arranged in a crust.
Chill several hours.

title: spinach salad
directions: Heat all ingredients together over medium heat.
Stir.
Add the following:

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon into deep hot fat fryer or large saucepan with hot oil.
Brown; drain.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar in pie pan.
Whip cooking oil and milk with fork.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Spread dough to shape of pie pan.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix dressing, taco seasoning, beans, onion and cheese in a large salad bowl.
Top with shredded lettuce and diced tomatoes. Just before serving, add crushed Doritos.
Toss well.

title: glazed poppy seed quick breadlincoln, nebraska
directions: Grease and flour loaf pans.

title: graham cracker crumb cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add graham cracker crumbs, baking powder, milk, coconut, pecans and vanilla. Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans at 325° for about 30 minutes or until done.

title: cherry cream cheese dessert
directions: Whip all ingredients well and pour into graham cracker crust.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, using only 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water in a mixing bowl.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in gelatin mixture and beat until smooth. Stir in vanilla extract, oranges, pineapple, lemon lime soda and pecans.
Fold in 3/4 whipped topping.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 1-inch dish.
Chill 4 hours or until set.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with remaining whipped topping.

title: red beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Keep in refrigerator.
Put beans in crock-pot; add all ingredients except for meat.
Fill to top with water.
Turn crock-pot on high.
Cook about 5 to 6 hours. Stir occasionally.
Add cut up sausage or browned ground beef. Sometimes I even add both.
Cook around 2 hours more or until your desired tenderness.
Serve with cornbread or over a bowl of white rice.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toast almonds at 400° for 5 minutes, until light brown. Combine all except almonds.
Marinate several hours in refrigerator.
Add almonds just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gumbo and rice(south carolina-style)
directions: Fry bacon, drain and set aside.
In bacon drippings, cook onions, stewed tomatoes, corn and okra until tender.
Add water if too thick (about 1 cup).
Crumble bacon and add to vegetables. Serve over rice.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix chopped cabbage and onions together and refrigerate. Melt margarine in skillet.
Add noodles and almonds and brown over low heat to golden color.
Add sesame seed when almost brown, set aside.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake about 45 minutes to 1 hour in 300° oven until bubbly.

title: neiman marcus squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and one egg; crumble into a 9 by 13 glass dish.
mix the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar, pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Pour oil in large baking pan.
Batter chops and place in pan in 400° oven.
Brown on both sides.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chops.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 1 hour.
Turn halfway through cooking time.

title: fried rice pilaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Saute for 10 minutes over low flame.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush together cookies.
Cream together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and margarine.
Mix vanilla instant pudding and milk.

title: parmesan fish
directions: Thaw fish.
Dip in egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Brown both sides in skillet with butter.
Add a little sauce to the bottom of a glass baking dish.
Place fish in pan.
Put a slice of cheese on top of fish, then sprinkle with mushrooms and green peppers.
Add enough sauce to cover.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: bacon and cheddar appetizers
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Mix all well and place a spoonful of mixture on small breads.
Put in broiler and brown.

title: sharon's macaroni salad
directions: Cook the macaroni for the maximum time.
Rinse macaroni with cold water as soon as finished cooking.
Add all ingredients.

title: mona newbern's strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix and cook figs and sugar.
After this starts to boil, cook for 20 minutes.
Add strawberry jello and Sure-Jell.
Let come to a boil and cook for 1 minute.
Put into scalded jars and seal.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix and bake 3/4 hour at 350° or until set.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except for cornbread mix.
Add cornbread mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: corny corn bread(children's)
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Pour into greased 7 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cauliflower fritters
directions: Chop cauliflower into small pieces.
Crush and chop the garlic.
Mix remaining ingredients into a batter.
If it is too thick add more milk.
Add cauliflower and garlic.
Drop by the spoonful into oil heated to 375°.
Cook until golden brown.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with vegetable oil cooking spray.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined milk, egg whites, applesauce and honey, mixing just until moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups almost full; bake 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown.
Store muffins in freezer.
To reheat, microwave at High about 30 seconds.
Each muffin (1 serving) is 120 calories; cholesterol 0 milligrams; fat 1 gram; sodium 90 milligrams; calcium 80 milligrams; dietary fiber 2 grams.

title: melissa's sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand in large mixing bowl. Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Don't overcook or they will be very dry.

title: ham and potato chowder
directions: In large saucepan, combine potato slices from mix, seasoning package, ham, carrot, pepper, water and milk.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium.
Cook 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Do not drain.
Stir in parsley.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend oleo, white sugar, brown sugar, vanilla, water and eggs together.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar; set aside.
Mix oleo, cocoa and water and bring to a boil.
Pour over flour mixture; mix well and add remaining ingredients and pour into 12 x 18-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: london broil teriyaki
directions: Combine oil, soy sauce, honey, vinegar, onion, garlic and ginger.
Pour over steak in shallow pan and marinate for at least 4 hours.

title: chicken papachush
directions: Slice onions and layer on bottom of crock-pot.
Put chicken pieces on top of onions.
Add salt, oil and paprika (no water). Place lid on crock-pot.
Set temperature on high.
Cook 2 hours. Turn chicken.
Finish cooking until done (approximately 4 hours). If cooking on stove top, cook on medium heat for 1 hour; turn chicken and finish cooking until done.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Mix crackers (crushed) and oleo.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: big-hearted coffeecake
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast into warm water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add milk mixture, eggs and 3 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic (10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl; grease top.
Cover. Let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled (1 hour). Roll
20 x 16-inches.
Brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle on sugars, fruits and nuts.
Roll as for jelly roll.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Shape into heart, joining ends at top. With scissors, cut two-thirds through roll at 1-inch intervals. Twist slices toward top.
Cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 350° (moderate) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with confectioners sugar icing; top with cherries.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook in a large skillet.
Cook hamburger and green pepper; drain meat.
Add both cans of soup plus 2 cans of water.
Add 1 cup rice.
Cook on medium heat until rice is done.
Also can be put in a casserole dish and cook in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt.
Add water and mix with whisk or fork.
Makes 2 bottom pie crusts.
Form into 2 balls.
Roll out on floured surface.

title: zucchini quiche(serves 6)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a large greased pie plate or quiche dish at 350 for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk together.
Roll out 1 package crescent roll dough; press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread filling over crust.
Place second crust over filling.
Brush with beaten egg white.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Dust with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: stuffed zucchini boats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Using a melon baller (or spoon), scoop out flesh of each zucchini half, leaving a shell about 1/4-inch thick.
Set zucchini aside.
Chop the pulp and set aside.

title: potato salad
directions: In bowl, combine potatoes, celery, pimentos, chives and parsley.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Add yogurt mixture to potato mixture and toss gently to coat; cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Toss again just before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers in baking pan.
Top with crackers.
Bake 20 minutes in a 375° oven.
Double recipe to fill a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: seasoned rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Place onion and margarine in greased casserole dish.
Add consomm, mushrooms, salt, pepper, rice and water.

title: hot mexican corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour half the batter into a hot greased 10 1/2-inch cast-iron skillet.
Sprinkle evenly with half the cheese.
Pour the remaining batter over cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites.
Cream egg yolks and sugar.
Add whiskey, beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
It's so thick you don't drink it, you eat it.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Cook roast until very tender.
Coarsely chop meat.
Add other ingredients and simmer at least 1 1/2 hours.

title: rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding the Kraft Italian dressing last, using just enough to moisten the ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Put in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve as a vegetable or instead of potatoes.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttered cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in 12 inch skillet that is at least 3 inches deep.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat to medium high. Cook for about 8 to 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender but not mushy.

title: strawberry delight
directions: 1st Layer: Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts together and press in dish (9 x 13). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: maxine's fluffy white icing
directions: Beat - Beat - Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.

title: oven mashed potatoes
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes according to directions on package.
Add seasoned salt, onion, basil, olives and cheese. Place in lightly greased rectangular casserole or baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup shredded cheese.
Bake in a 325° oven until cheese is melted, about 20 minutes.
Serves 12.
This can be made several hours ahead and refrigerated until baking.

title: 3 step cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well together. Add the eggs.
Blend well.
Pour into graham cracker crust (9-inch crust).
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool. Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Spread with 1 (21 ounce) can cherry pie filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onions; drain off fat.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Next, drain water off noodles; add to meat and add mushroom and celery soups, then drained corn and pimento. Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese. To this, crumble up crackers on top of cheese and top with melted butter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
This casserole should feed at least 8 people.
Very good to take to family dinner.

title: herbed cherry tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in a medium bowl; set aside. In a small bowl, combine oil and vinegar. Add parsley, basil, oregano, salt and sugar; mix well. Pour over the tomatoes. Cover and refrigerate for at least 3 hours. Drain; serve on lettuce, if desired. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes and boil until tender.
Cut off bad spots (leave jackets on); then chop into cubes.
Layer potatoes, bacon bits, cheese, butter and salt.
Repeat until all ingredients have been used.
Bake at 375° until cheese melts and serve warm.

title: chocolate walnut dollars
directions: Sift flour once; measure and add baking powder and cinnamon. Sift together 3 times.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add flour gradually.
Shape in 2-inch rolls; wrap in waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased sheet in hot oven, 400°, for 5 minutes.
Makes 8.

title: huckleberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk and egg yolks.
Fold in berries.
Beat egg whites and mix with other ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° until done.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Steam first 6 vegetables until crisp-tender.
In a skillet, saute the mushrooms and onion in 2 tablespoons butter for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook 1 minute more.
In a saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter. Add broth, cream, cheese, basil and red pepper. Cook until smooth and thickened. Add vegetables and cook until heated.
Add pasta and toss gently. Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet potatoes with apples
directions: Heat enough water to cover potatoes to boiling.
Add potatoes; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until tender, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool slightly; slip off skins.
Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Layer potatoes and apples in greased oblong baking dish (10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch).
Pour orange juice over potatoes and apples.
Mix brown sugar, ginger and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Dot with margarine.
Cook, uncovered, in a 350° oven until apples are crisp-tender, about 30 minutes.

title: mississippi grilled shrimp
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic; cook until softened, 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato sauce, brown sugar, crushed red pepper and lemon juice.
Bring to simmer, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat.
Place shrimp on hot barbecue grill rack; cook for 5 minutes, turning once and basting well with the sauce while cooking.
Drizzle any remaining sauce over shrimp to serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add pudding mix and milk.
Mix well; bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan and chill.
You may add nuts.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Mix peppers, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 or 2 minutes vigorously.
Set off stove for 5 minutes.
Add Certo. Mix well.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 7 1/2 pints.
Serve over cream cheese with crackers.

title: corn pie
directions: Peel corn and remove corn from cob.
Place corn in blender. Add raw eggs and oil; stir until smooth.
Separately brown hamburger.
Add onion; drain any liquid from the meat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add raisins.
Simmer for a couple of minutes.

title: cream and berries pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare pastry.
Heat milk to lukewarm. Mix sugar and flour together well in a bowl.
Pour milk over sugar and flour; mix well to remove any lumps.
Place washed berries into pastry lined pie plate.
Pour milk mixture carefully over berries.
If using, sprinkle very lightly with nutmeg.
Place pie in oven; drop temperature to 350°.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes, or until filling is set.
(Black raspberries may also be used, or 5 peaches, peeled and sliced also make a delicious peaches and cream pie.)

title: chicken pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in lightly greased 13x9x2-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken soup and broth and pour over chicken.
Arrange peas and carrots over top.
Mix flour and baking powder in bowl; add buttermilk and butter.
Stir to form a thin dough; pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Bake uncovered about 1 hour until crust rises to top and browns lightly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour melted butter over top. Cover with chips or flakes.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or when potatoes are done.

title: broccoli and tortellini salad
directions: Place bacon in a large deep skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown.
Drain, crumble and set aside.
Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Cook tortellini in boiling water for 8-10 minutes or until al dente.
Drain and rinse under cold water. In a large bowl, combine broccoli, tortellini, bacon, raisins, sunflower seeds and red onion.
Pour on dressing (recipe to follow) and toss.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Use only 1/2 of the juice from the peach halves.
Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil. Boil an additional 10 minutes.
Pour into a casserole dish and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: fettuccine alfredo with chicken
directions: Have all ingredients ready, as this dish needs to be served immediately.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel, slice and boil sweet potatoes in small amount of water. Drain, then mash.
Stir in milk, sugar, 1 stick of margarine, vanilla and eggs.
Stir all together and pour into large baking dish.
In bowl, cream together the brown sugar, 1 stick of margarine and flour, then stir in pecans.
Drop by tablespoonful over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: turkey loaves
directions: Combine all ingredients except barbecue sauce.
Mix well. Shape into 4 loaves.
Arrange loaves around edge of 1-quart casserole.
Cover and cook on 100% power for 7 to 9 minutes or until no longer pink.
Spoon barbecue sauce over loaves before serving.

title: festive florentine crescents
directions: Combine spinach, cheese, crumbs and bacon in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally. Unroll crescent roll dough; separate into 16 triangles.
Cut triangles into halves.
Spread each with rounded teaspoonful of spinach mixture.
Roll up from wide end.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 32 crescents.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in oleo with fork or pastry blender.
Add milk.
Mix to make a soft dough.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: the ultimate cheesecake
directions: Make graham cracker crust according to directions on box; spread in spring-form pan.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add marshmallows and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until marshmallows are melted and mixture is syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and stir until well coated.
Press warm mixture evenly and firmly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: meringue delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until dry and stiff.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add vanilla, almond extract and chocolate chips.
Cover cookie sheet with brown paper bag, drop mixture by spoonful on paper and turn heat off on oven before inserting cookie sheet.
Let stay overnight or until oven is completely cool.
This mixture doesn't change shape, so it can be put close together on cookie sheet.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar.
Refrigerate.
Use for short ribs; marinate overnight and charcoal broil.

title: black walnut pie
directions: Beat egg thoroughly with sugar, salt, syrup and melted margarine.
Add black walnuts.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted between center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
In another bowl, combine sugar, zucchini, oil, egg and lemon peel; mix well.
Add flour mixture and stir just until combined.
Pour batter into greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: lazy wife's chili soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine tomato juice and soup in pan or slow cooker. Add hamburger and beans; boil for 5 minutes. Turn down heat.
Add chili powder and pepper to taste.
This is a quick, easy, perfectly seasoned soup that tastes like it was simmered all day.
Serves 4.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla; blend thoroughly.
Stir in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 3 hours.

title: creamy pasta and vegetables
directions: Cook fettucine according to package directions, al dente. Blanch vegetables in boiling water 2 to 3 minutes (until crisp-tender).
Drain immediately.
Toss drained fettucine and vegetables gently; cover to keep warm.
Melt butter in a small saucepan; add garlic and saute about 30 seconds until golden. Remove from heat.
Stir in Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, milk, egg yolk, herbs and seasoning.
Cook about 3 minutes over low heat until hot; do not allow to boil.
Process cooked cheese mix in blender until smooth and creamy.
Pour over fettucine and vegetable mix.
Toss gently.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve at once.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Prepare salad in a large bowl. Add cheese.
Add beans and meat.
Crush chips and add.
Just before serving, add Catalina dressing.
Serve with taco sauce. Serve immediately.

title: crab dip
directions: While crab meat is draining, combine all the remaining ingredients in a large mixer bowl and beat until well blended. Fold in the crab meat.
Let dip set in refrigerator for at least one hour before serving.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine; set aside.
Heat soups (undiluted) and pour over cornbread crumbs.
Add onion and celery; mix well.
Season to taste (be careful with salt as soups are already salted).
Pour 1/2 of dressing into a greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Add chicken; top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage slightly.
Mix soup, sour cream, onions, pimento and water chestnuts.
Put cabbage in a buttered oblong pan.
Pour soup mixture over cabbage.
Top with bread crumbs and Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush the Oreo cookies very fine until the filling is gone; set aside.
Cream the margarine and cream cheese together; set aside. Mix sugar and Cool Whip.
Combine the milk, vanilla pudding and vanilla.
When set, add this to the margarine and cream cheese.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Place
pieces of soup bone in water to cover in a large pan. Season
with
salt.
Simmer several hours.
Remove meat, strain broth
and
place broth back into clean pan.
Cut meat into
bite size
pieces.
Add
vegetables,
tomato
paste and parsley. Season with rosemary leaves, basil, salt and pepper. Continue
to cook
for
30 to 45 minutes until vegetables are tender.

title: sandra's zucchini, carrot casserole
directions: Boil zucchini, onion and carrots together; drain water.
Add soup and sour cream.
Toss stuffing mix with melted butter.
Spread 1/2 stuffing mixture on bottom of 12 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top, then sprinkle rest of stuffing mix on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: yummy broccoli
directions: Heat water, garlic oil and garlic powder in saucepan.
Add broccoli.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes, until tender.
Add butter.

title: italian soup
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Cook vegetables until tender and mix all ingredients together.
You can stretch with V-8.
Add garlic salt, etc. to taste.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese when served.

title: bagels
directions: Blend water (warm), 1 1/2 cups flour, salt, sugar, yeast and onion chips for 3 minutes.
Add the rest of the flour and knead for 20 minutes.
Cover for 20 minutes.
Make into 24 bagels and cover for 20 minutes.
Boil each bagel for 3 minutes on each side. Spread egg white on top and sprinkle with poppy and sesame seed. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Makes 24 bagels.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and place in casserole. Mix sugar and flour; pour over pineapple. Add juice. Cover with cheese, then top with Ritz crumbs. Melt margarine and pour over top. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Grease and flour three 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and baking powder together.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Alternately add milk and flour until mixed thoroughly.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: almond custard no. 1
directions: Scald and blanch sweet almonds with bitter almonds, throwing them, as you do them, into a large bowl of cold water.
Then pound them one at a time into a paste, adding a few drops of wine or rose water to them.
Beat eggs very light with sugar, then mix altogether with milk; put the mixture into a saucepan and set it over the fire.
Stir it one way until it begins to thicken, but not until it curdles; remove from the fire and when it is cooled, put in a glass dish.
Having reserved part of the whites of the eggs, beat them to a stiff froth; season with sugar and lemon extract and spread over top of the custard.
Serve cold.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Cook sugar and milk together until soft ball stage on candy thermometer or soft ball in cold water.
Add chopped dates and butter and cook again until soft ball stage is reached.
Remove from stove and add nuts.
Stir as long as possible (thick) and pour onto damp cloth into a long roll; shape until it is set and roll in powdered sugar.
Wrap in wax paper and keep refrigerated. Slice when ready to eat.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice round steak thin and add all other ingredients except sour cream and bake for 4 hours at 300°.
When cooked, add 1 cup sour cream and mix well.
Serve on rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain well.
Combine all ingredients together and simmer until done.
May be served with grated cheese and sour cream.
Serve with taco chips.
Will freeze well.

title: butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together.
Add milk and flour mixture to the butter mixture. Cream together.
Bake at 350° until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Frost.

title: quick holiday fudge
directions: Melt margarine and cheese over low heat.
Add sugar and cocoa, vanilla and nuts.
Spread in 10 x 14-inch greased pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar; add eggs and vanilla. Add half amount of flour mixture with salt and soda. Add bananas.
Add balance of flour and the nuts. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil chicken until tender in water generously seasoned with seasoned salt.
Remove chicken and reserve broth.
Cook, skin and debone chicken.
Set aside.
Simmer onions, peppers and celery in 1 cup reserved broth until tender.
Cook spaghetti in remaining broth until just tender; drain and reserve broth.

title: lo-fat turkey cutlets
directions: Mix flour and bran cereal in large bowl.
Pound turkey cutlets flat with hand.
Dip each cutlet into egg substitute, then into flour mixture and coat well.

title: real mens cool creation
directions: In large bowl, put 4 (4 ounce) scoops of chocolate chip ice cream with 6 Oreo cookies around the top of bowl.
Serves 1.

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Mix lime jello according to pkg. instructions.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dissolve 1 cup of hot water and lemon Jello.
Add 30 marshmallows and let dissolve.
Mix 1/2 c. of sugar, whipped cream, cream cheese and pineapple.
Add this mixture to lemon Jello. After lime Jello has set, add lemon Jello mixture on top and let set.
Then dissolve red Jello as directed on pkg. and put on top of lemon mixture.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften Knox gelatine in the cold water.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add gelatine and stir to dissolve.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: creamed peas and new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut any large potatoes in half.
If desired, remove a narrow strip of peel from around the center of each potato.

title: cheesy onion sticks
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place a jellyroll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch) in oven with 1/3 cup margarine.
Allow to melt.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, milk, salt and garlic.
Pour mixture into jellyroll pan.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese, onion and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.
Cut crosswise into 1-inch strips.
Cut each strip crosswise in half.
Serve warm.

title: buttermilk cinnamon bars
directions: Combine the sugars, flour and butter.
Mix as you would for pastry.
Combine 2 cups of this mixture
with
coconut and nuts. Press lightly into the bottom of a	greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine remaining
ingredients.
Stir
in remaining butter mixture and spread over first
layer
in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes while still	warm.
Frost
with
a thin powdered sugar icing.
Cut into bars.

title: low-fat dumplings
directions: Shred chicken and set aside.
Chill stock overnight.
Scope off fat.
Heat remaining stock, broth, soup and chicken.
Break uncooked noodles and add to mixture.
Add parsley and basil.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until noodles are plump and soup thickens.
tags: Healthy Choice cream of chicken soup

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and mix well the ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: honey raisin bran muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; set aside. In large bowl, stir together cereal, milk and honey.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes until cereal is softened.
Add egg and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until moistened.
Pour batter into 12-muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes or until browned.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly in a large mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup crushed wafers and put the rest of the crumbs in an 8 x 8-inch pan. Cream the oleo and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and spread over crumbs.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Spread with berries, then whipped cream.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup wafer crumbs over the whipped cream.
Place in the refrigerator to set before using.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until thick; stir in oil.
Sift all dry ingredients together; stir into egg mixture.
Fold carrots, nuts, pineapple and coconut into batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon stick punch
directions: Pour apple cider and cranberry juice in a 30 cup percolator. Place cinnamon sticks, cloves and brown sugar in the basket of percolator.
Let perk.
Serve hot.
Remove mixture from basket and simmer in small pan of water for a delightful spice scent in your home.

title: mama's vegetable soup
directions: Mix above ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: louisiana shrimp mold supreme
directions: Combine cream cheese and mushroom soup.
Cook on low heat until smooth.
Add green onions, celery, shrimp, mayonnaise, Tabasco and red pepper.
Stir until mixed.
Dissolve gelatine in lemon juice.
Add to mixture and blend in well.
Pour into mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Can also be served with crackers as an appetizer.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, beating in a little at a time.
Add nuts, then dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Make into loaves; wrap in wax paper and place in refrigerator overnight.
Slice and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Add together the sugar, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and raisins. Add this to the beaten eggs.
Pour this all over the bread cubes that have been put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place in a larger pan with 1/2-inch of water in it.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour, until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put uncooked white rice in the bottom of a roasting pan or deep baking dish.
Place chopped onion on top.
Add 1 cup of water.
Arrange chicken pieces on top of rice and pour cans of soup over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven until chicken is tender, about 1 hour.

title: chocolate crunch candy
directions: Melt chocolate. Add peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Beat eggs well. Add milk, pumpkin and spices.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the cake mix evenly over the pumpkin mix. Sprinkle the chopped nuts and spread the oleo over this.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese sauce
directions: Mix all items together. Simmer a few minutes.
Pour over vegetables (broccoli, potatoes or cauliflower).

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into baking dish; dot with butter. Bake at 350° until set, approximately 45 minutes.

title: manwich night meat loaf
directions: In a bowl mix first 6 ingredients with 1/2 cup sauce.
Shape into a loaf and place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; drain.
Spread mustard over loaf and pour remaining sauce over all.
Bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: little willies
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage, oregano and peppers together. Drain and set aside.
In a large microwave bowl, melt the cheese. Add the meat with the cheese; mix well.
Spread a little of the mixture on each piece of bread; put on cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes at 375°.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo; add butter, extracts and nuts.
Pour over flour, eggs, sugar and vanilla and mix well.
Bake at 350° until top cracks.
Does not need icing.

title: zucchini quesadillas
directions: Grate zucchini into large shreds. Slice onion into thin strips. Heat olive oil in medium skillet and slowly saute onion and garlic about 8 minutes.

title: kate campbell's gouda cheese appetizers
directions: Roll out the crescent dough. Spread with mustard.
Peel whole Gouda and place in center of dough.
Seal the Gouda with dough to cover it completely. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until browned. Serve with sliced apples, crackers or chips or eat "as is."

title: boiling water
directions: Fill saucepan with water.
Place on burner on high heat.
When water has rolling bubbles, it is ready.
Add salt at beginning if for veggies.
Use no salt if for coffee or tea.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: wade cake
directions: Soften yeast in lukewarm water.
Blend together the sugar, salt and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add lukewarm milk and yeast.
Gradually add flour, mixing thoroughly until a smooth dough is formed.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: *Or 10 ounce package berries, thawed and reduce sugar to 2/3 cup.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture into well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Pour rest of mixture in pan and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 475°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer-2 minutes or until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating 5-7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow disappears. Add vanilla, mixing well. Combine flour and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating on low speed just until blended after each addition. Pour batter into a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Fill a 2 cup ovenproof measuring cup with water and place in oven with tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10-15 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.

title: "alfredo" chicken and broccoli
directions: Microwave:
In 2-quart dish, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Microwave, uncovered, at High 13 to 14 minutes.
Stir in chicken.
Heat 1 minute.
Cover and let stand 2 minutes.

title: tomato macaroni salad
directions: Mix together and add to above.
Cool and keep in refrigerator. Serve with crackers and cheese, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: quick mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and red pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti with white clam sauce
directions: In a large skillet, saute garlic in oil until brown.
Discard garlic.
Add parsley, salt and pepper.
Drain juice from clams and add to oil mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Add clams and heat through. Cook pasta.
Toss with butter.
Top with 1/2 clam sauce.
Serve with remaining sauce and grated cheese.
Serves 4.

title: dressing for wilted cabbage or lettuce
directions: Bake spareribs in oven at 450° for 45 minutes until brown. Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake until done, 1 1/2 hours.

title: stephen's homemade meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together; fry on low heat until done.
Add to favorite sauce.

title: spiced apple butter
directions: Pare, core and quarter apples.
In large kettle, combine apples and cider.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Puree apples through food processor.
Add sugar and spices.
Mix well.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until thickened when spooned.
Pour into 1/2-pint jars.
Put in hot water bath. Half cover jars.
Boil 10 minutes.
Makes 7 half pints.

title: nora townsend's date pudding
directions: Add butter or margarine to boiling water.
Pour over dates and let stand while mixing dry ingredients for batter.
Combine sugar, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add dates and liquid to mixture.
Add egg and walnuts to batter and mix.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake per directions on box.
Before cake is done, mix sugar and pineapple and boil 5 minutes.
Pour over hot cake.
Cool cake.
Mix pudding according to directions on box and spread over cake.
Spread on Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans or coconut or both or without either.

title: cheddar cheese fudge
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Combine all in a large bowl.
Beat until creamy.
May need 1/4 cup milk if too day. Put into buttered 9-inch square pan.
When firm, cut into 64 pieces.
Makes about 3 1/2 pounds.

title: spring dessert
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until tested done.
Cool cake completely.

title: six-week bran muffins
directions: Mix bran flakes, sugar, flour, salt, soda and beaten eggs.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Stir by hand and mix well.
Put in dish; cover and place in refrigerator.
Do not stir again.
Fill muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Mixture will keep for 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1/2 cup milk with soft cream cheese.
Mix pudding with remainder of milk (1 1/2 cups).
Add cheese mixture.
Spread over cooled cake.
Spread pineapple over that, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut on top. Refrigerate.

title: black pasta with calamari
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water with 1 teaspoon olive oil, cook pasta until just tender, 3 to 4 minutes, or according to package directions.
Drain pasta and place in an attractive serving dish.
Cover with foil and keep warm.
In same pan, heat remaining 1/4 cup oil and butter over medium-high heat until butter is melted.
Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 10 to 15 seconds.
Stir in calamari and cook 1 minute.
Pour over pasta; toss to combine.
Sprinkle cheese over top and serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 2-quart casserole. Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins and caraway (if used).
Add buttermilk and all but one tablespoon of the eggs.
Mix until flour is moistened (dough will be sticky).
Turn out on floured surface.
Rub flour on hands and knead to mix thoroughly (about 10 strokes).
Shape into a ball and place in casserole.
With sharp knife, cut a 4-inch cross, 1/4 inch deep.
Brush with egg.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes, until center is done. Cool 10 minutes. Remove; cool completely.

title: chocolate-peanut butter treats
directions: Beat together butter, sugar and peanut butter until very dry. Fold Rice Krispies in.
Press into foil-lined miniature muffin cups, filling each about 3/4 full.
Melt morsels in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, or melt in microwave.
Spread about 1 teaspoon chocolate over each Rice Krispies mixture.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until chocolate hardens.

title: holiday marinated vegetables
directions: Pour dressing over Brussels sprouts and tomatoes in large glass or plastic bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours but no longer than 24 hours.
Add mushrooms to vegetables; toss until well coated.
Drain before serving.
Serve vegetables on lettuce.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, boil bouillon cubes in water until dissolved. Add diced vegetables.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Next, add cheese and soup to vegetable broth mixture.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Do not boil as cheese will scorch.

title: hershey's great american chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In large mixer bowl cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts if desired. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until very lightly browned.
Cool slightly, remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yields about 6 dozen cookies.

title: chuck pot roast in foil
directions: Put meat in foil with both soups on top (cream first and then powdered dry).
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Potatoes may be baked in the foil with the meat as well as carrots, diced 1-inch size. Fold foil over top and at ends, and seal to cook.
Makes the gravy - no mess!

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients (add broth last).
Dressing should be that of a mushy consistency, then bake in oven at 375 degrees for about an hour or until top gets lightly brown and starts to get dry.

title: peanut butter chocolate fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, melt peanut butter chips, 1 cup Eagle Brand and 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir occasionally. Remove from heat. Stir in nuts. Spread into an 8-inch square pan sprayed with Pam.
In a small saucepan, melt chocolate, remaining milk and butter.
Spread on top of peanut butter mixture. Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store tightly covered.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix and place in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (only use 1/2 cup butter).
Take the crushed cornflakes and mix with the remaining 1/4 cup butter and sprinkle on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large jar.
Shake well and chill.

title: george washington chowder
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until soft.
Add next 2 ingredients. Reheat and add last 2 ingredients.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Brown celery and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients well. Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together in large mixing bowl or blender. Add all other ingredients, except whole pecans, and mix well. Pour mixture evenly into uncooked pie shells.
Top with whole pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: easiest lemon pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and the thawed lemonade together and add Cool Whip.
Pour in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: poke salad and eggs
directions: Wash greens carefully several times.
Cook in handful of salt until tender.
Drain and rinse several times.
Put 2 cups in skillet with some bacon grease and cook until all water is out. Add salt.
Add beaten egg and scramble in poke.

title: mexican beans
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Add to pre-soaked beans in pot with sufficient water.
Cook over low heat until tender.
It is good with Mexican cornbread.

title: asparagus mold
directions: Bring soup to boil and stir in Jell-O.
Remove from heat and add cheese and onion; mix together.
Add water and salad dressing and mix well.
Then stir in green peppers, nuts and celery.
Pour into mold and chill until set up.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush oreos in food processor (set aside). Mix cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar, milk, pudding and cool whip in plastic flower pot lined with foil. Put a small amount of crushed cookies in bottom of pot.
Layer pudding/cookies/pudding/cookies ending with cookies. Top with a bouquet of silk flowers. Serve with new garden trowel.

title: zucchini
directions: Saute onions, green peppers and garlic 2 minutes in olive oil. Stir in ground beef; cook until browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Turn into 1-quart casserole.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: evelyn's hot sauce
directions: Pour tomatoes from
can
into
blender	and
blend to a pulp. Add remaining ingredients
to tomato pulp and heat to a boil.
Let cool.
Flavor
is	improved if made a day ahead of using.	Will keep in refrigerator for a week.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package in a 13 x 9 pan. Place frozen candy bars in a large Ziploc bag and crush to fine crumbs. Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip in large glass bowl and set aside. In a large glass Pyrex dish, layer the following: Crumble just enough cake to cover the bottom of dish, then spoon layer of Cool Whip mix, then sprinkle layer of candy crumbles. Repeat layers as long as ingredients last, ending with the Butterfinger crumbs. Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot rods appetizer
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Refrigerate until used.
Spread on rye bread and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: creamed chicken and shrimp
directions: Saute onion, peppers, parsley and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, mixing well.
Add chicken broth and cream. Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add chicken, shrimp and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crumble
vanilla wafers and melt margarine.
Pour margarine
over
crumbled
wafers
and blend. Put crumbled wafers in 8-inch
aluminum
pie
pan and press to make pie shell.
Line pie pan with whole wafers.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Blend cake mix, Cool Whip and eggs together and chill.
Drop by teaspoon in powdered sugar and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
You can use any cake mix.

title: pork chop 'n stuffing
directions: *Stove Top or Pepperidge Farm stuffing may be used.

title: corn delicious
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add milk gradually.
Then add corn, salt, pepper and sugar.
Let come to boiling point.
Set off heat and cool.
Beat eggs well.
Beat into corn mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: yellow cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs 2 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and flavoring.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add to mixture last.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Let cool before icing with caramel or peanut butter icing.

title: apple raisin bread pudding
directions: Mix apples, bread, raisins and white sugar together.
Mix eggs, milk and vanilla and add to apple mixture.
Put in a buttered 8 x 8 casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and rub into crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of pudding and bake until golden brown at 350 degrees.
Serve warm with ice cream or plain cream.

title: grama julia's beef soup(hungarian style)
directions: Wash meat and bones.
Place in large pot.
Add water.
Let it come to a boil; skim off fat.
Prepare vegetables by washing and paring as necessary.
Add seasoning and vegetables except potatoes.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Add whole potatoes; simmer for another 1/2 hour.
When done, strain soup.
Serve as consomme or with Crum Noodles.

title: christmas brunch eggs(good any morning)
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs and milk, mix well. Pour over bread cubes.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper. Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chopped raisin cake
directions: Pour the boiling water and soda over the raisins; let stand while mixing the remaining ingredients.
Mix all together, stirring until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured small cake pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and the 2 tablespoons flour and hold. Heat milk and
cup
sugar.
Add
the
eggs, which have been beaten. Add the sugar-flour mixture.
Cook in a double boiler until thick enough
to
coat a spoon, or thicker, if desired. Cool and add vanilla.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice; add pineapple, coconut, pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix well; put into graham cracker crumb crust. (If you use a small pie crust, this will make 2 pies.)

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Fold in vanilla and Ritz crackers.
Add pecans and pour into buttered pie pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool overnight.

title: reese's cup cake
directions: Mix margarine, cocoa, buttermilk, water and eggs in saucepan. Almost bring to a boil (do not boil).
Take off stove and add sugar, flour and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: cinnamon honey scones
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, baking powder and cinnamon in a mixing bowl.
Add margarine to flour mixture and work it in. Add honey, milk and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Put spoonfuls of dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly golden brown.
Makes 8 scones.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers, cut in half and clean.
Cook for about 10 minutes in boiling water.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add 1/2 sauce, salt, pepper, garlic, onion and rice.
Dip into peppers, pour rest over peppers.
Sprinkle a little more garlic over top of peppers.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: polenta gnocchi
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients (according to cornmeal package directions) until smooth and very thick.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in egg and 1 tablespoon butter or oleo.
Lightly moisten cookie sheet or large serving platter with water; spread cornmeal mixture evenly to 1/2-inch layer.
Cool.
Cut into rounds with 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter to make gnocchi.
Arrange gnocchi in slightly overlapping rows in lightly buttered baking dish. Lightly brush with melted butter; sprinkle with sage leaves and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until puffed and brown, about 25 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Blend onion, sugar and vinegar 5 minutes.
Add mustard, salt and oil and beat 10 minutes.
Stir in poppy seed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together in bowl.
At last minute, prepare 1 cup mayonnaise, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons vinegar.
Mix with vegetables.
May also add chopped cauliflower with vegetables. May double the ingredients.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in closed container.
Use 1 or more heaping tablespoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: justin's cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain.
In large bowl, whip together potatoes, cheese, salt and butter.

title: hot spiced punch
directions: Place all juices and the sugar in a coffee percolator; stir. Place spices in top rack of percolator. Brew like coffee. Remove spices when brewing cycle finishes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix sugar, allspice and cloves.
Throughly drain the pickles. Place alternate layers of the pickles in a 2 1/2-quart jar with sugar mixture between each layer.
Place lid on jar.
Place in refrigerator.
These pickles will now make their own syrup and will be ready to serve in 4 days.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together with hands.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
(Can be made ahead and frozen.)

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and eggs; cut up and put in pan.
Mix soup and broth.
Pour over chicken and eggs.
Mix butter (melted), milk and self-rising flour.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: haddock with crumb topping
directions: Put fish in buttered flat casserole dish to just fit. Sprinkle with salt and lemon juice.
Let stand for 30 minutes. Mix onion with mayonnaise and spread over fish.
Mix crumbs, seasoning and cheese, sprinkle over top.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until well browned and fish is white and firm.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook celery and onions in butter.
Mix milk and Cheez Whiz over medium heat.
Cook broccoli in separate pan, drain off water. Combine all ingredients.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan or a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in large pan and cook to soft ball.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until creamy and pour quickly into greased pan.
Never fail!!

title: "girdle buster" peanut pie
directions: Soften and beat coffee ice cream.
Pour into a graham cracker crust and freeze.
When firm, spread chocolate fudge sauce over top and sprinkle with nuts.
Keep frozen until time to serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening until like coarse crumbs.
Add milk and mix to make soft dough.
Knead lightly (about 10 times) on lightly floured surface.
Roll dough out to 1/2 to 3/4 inch thickness with floured rolling pin.
Cut dough with large size biscuit cutter. Place oil in pan.
Let warm in oven while cutting biscuits.
Take pan from oven and touch the top of biscuit in oil in pan.
Place it in pan.
Repeat with each biscuit.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade yeast free bread
directions: Put all ingredients into a medium bowl.
Beat with eggbeater until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan and bake at 360° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 1 standard bread size loaf.

title: cinnamon monkey bread
directions: Roll quartered biscuits into balls.
Roll balls in cinnamon-sugar.
Place in greased tube pan.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with other ingredients, using only 1 cup nuts.
Shape into 2 balls and roll in other cup of chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: sandwich filling #1
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on bread or roll.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and flour.
Stir in milk slowly.
Blend well with sugar and butter, which has been creamed together.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in slow oven at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: spinach madeline
directions: Saute butter, flour and chopped onion.
Add spinach liquid and remaining ingredients, except spinach.
Stir until cheese melts. Add cooked spinach.
Top with bread crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 15 minutes).
May be made ahead and frozen.
Thaw thoroughly before cooking.

title: green bean and cheese casserole
directions: Combine margarine and flour; cook gently.
Remove from fire and stir in seasonings and sour cream.
Fold in drained beans and place in casserole and sprinkle with cheese, then top with French fried onions.
Bake in a 350° oven until heated thoroughly.

title: applesauce pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool right side up about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, then dry ingredients.
Mash bananas and add to batter.
Bake slowly in Bundt pan at 375° for one hour.

title: crock pot lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and seasoning in skillet. Drain. Combine spaghetti sauce and water in a small bowl. Place 4 noodles in the bottom of a lightly greased slow cooker. Layer with half of beef mixture, spaghetti sauce mixture, and mushrooms. Spread ricotta over mushrooms. Sprinkle with 1 cup mozzarella. Layer with remaining noodles, meat, sauce, mushrooms, and cheese. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour. Reduce and cook on low for 5 hours.

title: best-ever banana bread
directions: Mix bananas in mixer.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients;
mix.	Bake
in
greased loaf pans at 300° for 60 minutes, or until wooden toothpick comes out dry.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and Crisco until fluffy. Add sugar and beat until light.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add flour, milk, vanilla and pineapple juice.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Lay the pork chops in a baking dish.
In a bowl, hand crush the tomatoes, then add water, salt, pepper, garlic and sliced pepper.
Mix and pour over the pork chops.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles and place in cool water to handle; drain. Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and begin layering as follows.
Place 3 strips noodles on bottom of pan, 1/3 of the cottage cheese spooned evenly, 1/3 of the Mozzarella cheese and 1/3 of the beef and sauce mixture.
Repeat for 2 more layers.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and rinse until cool.
Toss with Italian dressing.
Better if made the night before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and cool.
Mix other ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper. Brown in oil in skillet. Place in baking dish or casserole. Cover with rice.

title: cream puffs
directions: Add butter to water; heat until butter melts.
Add flour, all at once, and stir until ball forms in center of pan.
Remove from stove; let stand five minutes.
Add eggs, beating after adding each egg (batter should be stiff).
Shape onto buttered cookie sheet by dropping by spoonfuls.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: tandoori chicken
directions: With a small, sharp knife, cut 1/2 inch deep slits about 1 inch apart in chicken.
Place chicken in 1 gallon size food storage bag.
Add lemon juice.
Toss chicken to coat with juice. Mix the remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour into bag to coat chicken.
Rub marinade into slits, or use hands to coat chicken.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or preferably overnight. Line a broiler pan with foil for easy cleanup.
Lightly oil the rack of broiler pan.
Arrange chicken, skin side down, on rack. Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat source for 20 minutes, then turn over and broil 10 to 15 minutes longer, until juices run clear.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Microwave margarine and chocolate in a 1-quart microwave-safe bowl 2 minutes or until melted, stirring once. Beat eggs adding sugar. Mix well. Add flour and vanilla. Stir in chocolate mixture and nuts. Grease 13 x 9 pan. Pour mixture into pan and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: quickie salad
directions: Dump all ingredients together and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Use as a salad or dessert.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cut bacon into 1 inch lengths and put into soup kettle.
Add onion and cook until onion is soft and bacon done.
Add potatoes, corn and water.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add margarine, milk and seasonings.
Reheat to boiling and serve piping hot. Serves 5.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and drain. Place rice in bottom of baking dish. Add browned pork chops. Blend tomatoes and bouillon in blender (may substitute tomato juice). Pour over pork chops and rice. Add onion slices and green pepper rings. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: appetizer pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread in 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish and bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until brown. Allow to set.
Reheat just before serving.
Serve with crackers. (Recipe can be doubled.)

title: hot crab appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Heat in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: swiss cheese and vegetable pie
directions: Saute onions, mushrooms and broccoli in butter until onions are tender.
Drain off excess liquid.
Place vegetables in pie crust.
Place grated cheese on top of vegetables.
Combine eggs, flour, salt, and milk.
Mix well.
Pour egg mixture over cheese and vegetables.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Let cool 2 -3 minutes before serving.
Also good cold.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Mix the dry ingredients. Add beaten eggs, pineapple (with juice) and oil and blend well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter.
Pour into greased 10 x 13 inch pan.
Pour melted butter on top and bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rancher beans
directions: Brown beef; saute onion in margarine until browned.
Add salt, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine sugar and catsup, add to beans and mix with meat mixture.
Put in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put
in 1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 1 hour	at 300°.
Serve hot on snack crackers.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Add garlic salt, tomato paste, sauce, oregano, basil and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Beat eggs; add cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: easy cheesy tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Mix with tuna, carrots, peas, onion and cheese sauce thoroughly.
Pour into baking dish sprayed with Pam, etc.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until edges begin to brown.

title: spinach dip
directions: Blend all ingredients well. Refrigerate.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: Cook beans until just tender.
Drain.
While beans are cooking, fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Add onion to bacon drippings and cook until tender (not brown) over low heat.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and finely crumbled bacon.
Pour over hot beans.

title: chocolate muffins(weight watchers)
directions: Mix together.
Spray muffin pan.
Cook according to muffin directions on back of cake mix box.

title: leftovers pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Chill before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tempting topping(an old recipe)
directions: In a medium bowl, with an electric mixer, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla, beating until fluffy.
Add powdered sugar gradually and continue beating until smooth and creamy.
Use to frost one 9-inch cake or the tops of two 9-inch layers.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in 3-quart saucepan over moderate heat until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in rice cereal.
Press into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let harden.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over cereal mixture.
Chill about 5 minutes.

title: baked curried chicken salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix chicken, celery, cheese, mayonnaise, onion and lemon juice in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Melt margarine, stir in bread crumbs, paprika and curry powder.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Defrost strawberries.
Do not drain but slice them.
Drain pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add strawberries, bananas, pineapple and nuts.
Divide mixture in half.
Pour one portion in container and let congeal.
Spread sour cream over the congealed portion; pour remaining Jell-O mixture in container. Return to refrigerator until completely congealed.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix together and press in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or so. Cool.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend oleo, salt, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 2 cups flour to make soft dough.
Press evenly into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until golden.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Place all ingredients except the okra in a large heavy stockpot and bring to a boil. Lower the heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Add the okra and continue to simmer over medium heat for 10 minutes longer. Remove the gumbo from the heat and refrigerate it overnight so that the flavors will blend. When ready to serve, reheat it, again being careful not to allow it to come to a boil. Remove the bay leaves and serve hot over a scoop of white rice.

title: cream corn
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot (no need to thaw corn).
Stir occasionally while cooking.
Needs about 2 to 2 1/2 hours in crock-pot.
Spray sides of crock-pot with Pam to prevent sticking.

title: applesauce squares
directions: Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch pan.
Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy at medium speed.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture.
Add applesauce, nuts and raisins, stirring with a spoon until well mixed.
Turn into pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Spread thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch
pan; mix remaining ingredients in a pan and heat until cheese melts.
Then pour over potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: martha washington
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and add coconut and pecans. Roll in little balls and chill.

title: chicken in a bun
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix cream cheese and chives with melted butter, add a little mayonnaise for moistness.
Flatten out crescent rolls, leaving 2 together.
Mix cream cheese mixture with cooked chicken.
Put a quarter of the mixture in each crescent roll. Pinch corners together.
Brush melted butter across the top of each bun.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Take large bowl and beat 2 eggs until fluffy (mix by hand). Add crushed pineapple (juice and all); mix slowly.
Add sugar, brown and white, then slowly add flour and baking soda.
Do not mix fast because you will make air pockets, then add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Bake in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Check with knife; must be clean, then let cool in pan.
Cut in 2 1/2-inch squares.
Take out of pan with spatula. Place on plate.

title: st. patrick's day buffet style corned beef hash
directions: Combine beef hash and onion in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Pour cream over hash.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°. Remove and arrange 16 deviled egg halves on hash.
Serve with heated chili sauce or catsup in pepper pots.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: shrimp cream cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, tiny shrimp, horseradish and onion and form into a ball.
Mix ketchup, lemon juice and horseradish and pour on top of ball.
Place ball on bed of bib lettuce.
Serve with Ritz or Clubhouse crackers.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together water, egg and vinegar.
Then, add salt, flour and shortening.
Form into a dough ball.
This recipe may be refrigerated for up to 5 days.
It makes 5 pie crusts.

title: chili and tortilla pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Fry tortillas in oil, 5 to 10 seconds on each side.
Spread refried beans 1/4-inch thick on 4 tortillas. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons each onion and pepper over beans; top with 1/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese.
Place a second tortilla on top of each prepared tortilla pie.
Crumble ground beef very fine.
Stir in chili sauce.
Spoon beef mixture on top of second tortilla, about 1/2 cup per pie.
Top each pie with 1/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese.
Place a third tortilla on top of each prepared tortilla pie.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons each onion and pepper; top with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese melts.
Garnish with sour cream and paprika, if desired. Makes 6 individual pies.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Prepare crust for 1 pie.
Mix together 2 tablespoons flour, 3/4 cup sugar and the salt.
Add egg, vanilla, sour cream and nutmeg.
Beat to a smooth batter.
Stir in apples.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
Remove from oven.

title: mallow fruit salad
directions: Toss orange segments, pineapple chunks, cherries and marshmallows with lemon juice.
Prepare topping mix as directed on package.
Fold into fruit; cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: deluxe cheese mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Blend in sherbet.
Chill until very thick.
Stir in cottage cheese.
Put in 1-quart mold. Chill until firm.

title: devil pickles
directions: Slice pickles.
Layer with ice in ice chest or crock.
Let set one day.
Drain.
Layer pickles, spices, garlic and sugar.
Pour Tabasco and vinegar over layers.
Cover and let set for three days, stirring once a day.
Pack into jars.
No processing necessary.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix Veg-All, soups and 1 1/2 cans of chicken broth (saved from cooked chicken).
Line dish with cut-up chicken (bite size pieces) and pour all other ingredients over chicken.
For crust, mix together flour, milk, water, margarine and pepper and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: aunt susan's cornbread stuffing
directions: Mix stuffing, corn bread, celery, and onion together.
Mix in broth until mixture is moist.

title: low-fat seafood salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Serve salad in tomato cups or on a bed of romaine lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water with garlic salt.
Cook broccoli in a small amount of salted water, just until bright green, but not mushy.
Line bottom of casserole dish with broccoli.
Cut chicken in chunks and place on top of broccoli. Mix soup, cheese, mayonnaise and lemon juice thoroughly.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs or crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot.

title: sugar rolled kolacky
directions: Sift flour and cut in shortening until very fine crumbs.

Add rest of ingredients and work until dough leaves sides of bowl. Divide into sections. Roll out on granulated sugar. Cut in squares and fill with filling of choice. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until nice and brown.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and keep in a tightly covered jar. Use as you would instant tea.
Very good hot!

title: yummy french toast
directions: Mix egg, milk, vanilla, cinnamon and sugar.
Dip bread in batter; cook in hot skillet with butter.
Syrup is not needed.

title: panzit
directions: In skillet, brown together the oil, garlic buds, tomatoes, garlic powder and onion.
Add meat and other ingredients; cook until vegetables are done.
Serve with fine spaghetti or rice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Put in plastic bag.
Pinch each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Put into bag and shake until well coated.

title: tabouli
directions: Soak wheat for 10 to 12 minutes in cold water.
Squeeze water out; place in refrigerator.
Wash all greens; dry, slice and dice. Mix spices with juice of lemons and oil.
Chop tomatoes.
Add all ingredients to wheat; mix thoroughly.
Serve with romaine lettuce, toasted pita bread, etc.

title: scalloped potatoes for crock-pot
directions: Put half of Smokies, potatoes and onion in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and half the shredded Cheddar.
Spoon 1 can cream of mushroom soup on these ingredients.
Repeat with remaining half of ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours (or High 4 hours).

title: diabetic fresh apple cake
directions: Combine flour, oats, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and baking soda.
Set aside.
Cream margarine.
Add egg, vanilla, apple juice concentrate and Sugar Twin.
Stir in flour mixture to blend.
