Add diced apples, nuts and raisins.
Spray an 8 x 12-inch baking dish with Pam.
Add batter, spreading evenly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick cranberry salad
directions: Layer ingredients in bowl and refrigerate.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Drain broccoli and add to melted cheese.
Saute onion and celery in butter until golden brown.
Add to cheese mixture.
Add soup and blend all.
Some Ro-Tel tomatoes with green chilies may be added for spice.

title: lee gibson's specialty
directions: Place Doritos on a pizza pan.
Grate the cheese and sprinkle on top of Doritos.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Top with chopped hot peppers.
Heat under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: gourmet broccoli
directions: Cook fresh broccoli in boiling salted water until tender-crisp.
Drain and chop coarsely.
(Cook frozen broccoli as directed on package and then drain.)
Make white sauce by blending butter, flour, chicken stock base and salt.
Add milk and cook until thickened.
Make stuffing according to package directions, adding nuts if desired.
Mix.
Put broccoli into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour white sauce over and top with stuffing. Press down slightly.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mel's sweet and sour baked beans
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Drain on paper towels, then crumble and set aside.
Slice onions and separate into rings and cook in bacon drippings until tender but NOT brown.
Stir in brown sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt, and vinegar.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Drain butter, lima, and kidney beans.
Combined with baked beans, onion mixture, and bacon into a three quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for about one hour.

title: hamburger parmesan
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make patties.
Broil in oven.
Melt grated mixed Mozzarella and mild Cheddar on top.
Cooking time: approximately 35 minutes.

title: shrimp linguini
directions: Cook pasta in a large pot of boiling water.
Meanwhile, melt butter in a large skillet.
Add shrimp, mushrooms and garlic. Cook over medium-high heat, stirring often, until shrimp are cooked, about 5 minutes.
Place linguini in a serving bowl.
Pour shrimp mixture over the linguini.
Sprinkle with the cheese, salt and pepper.
Toss well.
Serve immediately.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: cendye's christmas ham
directions: Place ham in baking pan. Pour Coke over ham, place pineapple and cherries around over ham, using toothpicks to hold in place. Pour some of the pineapple and cherry juice over ham. Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at lowest oven setting overnight. I usually put mine on about 11pm and take it out first thing Christmas morning.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, except pie shells.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberries brulee
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat the cream cheese with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add sour cream and 2 tablespoons brown sugar; beat until smooth.
Reserve 1 strawberry for garnish.
Halve remaining berries and arrange evenly in the bottom of a shallow 8-inch broiler-proof dish.
Spoon the cream cheese mixture over berries.
Sieve the 1/4 cup brown sugar evenly over cream cheese mixture.
Broil 4 to 5 inches from heat for 1 to 2 minutes, or until sugar turns golden brown.
Slice reserved berry; arrange atop dessert.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: fun to make popcorn balls
directions: Keep popped corn warm in a slow oven (300°).
Combine sugar, Karo, water, salt and vinegar.
Cook to 250°; add the vanilla. Pour syrup slowly over warm corn.
Stir slowly and gently.
Butter hands and make into balls.
Wrap in wax paper.

title: apple salad
directions: Beat egg with milk.
Mix cornstarch and sugar together and add milk and egg.
Cook, stirring constantly.
Bring to boil and cook just a few minutes.
Remove from stove and cool slightly.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
(Be sure to cool as vinegar tends to curdle if hot.)
Refrigerate before using with fruit.
Will keep a week in fridge.

title: fruity white fudge
directions: Melt chocolate morsels and add milk.
Add nuts and candied fruit.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 inch pan.
Let set and cut, delicious!

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix flour and butter until crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan for bottom crust.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and mustard.
Put buttered bread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Crumble layers of sausage and cheese over bread; repeat layering. Pour milk mixture over all.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake about 45 minutes at 375°.
Bacon may be used; more eggs may be used.

title: broccoli ham ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Coarsely chop ham, broccoli, onion and parsley. Mix all ingredients except crescent rolls and set aside. Arrange crescent triangles in a circle on a 13-inch baking stone with bases overlapping in center and points to the outside. Evenly spoon filling over base. Fold points of triangles over filling and tuck under base at center. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Clean and cut up vegetables.

title: sherry cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for 6 minutes with electric mixer. Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes if using a Bundt pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cream cheese should be soft; blend well with sweetened condensed milk.
(You can use more than 4 tablespoons of milk, depending on how sweet you want it.)
Drain juice from canned fruit well (use fruits in their own juices).
Blend all ingredients together in a dish.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: date loaf
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Add dates and cook 4 minutes longer.
Remove from stove and add nuts and butter.
Beat until creamy.
Then roll out on a damp cloth and wrap in a roll. Slice when ready to serve.

title: squash fritters
directions: Stir together by hand.
Drop by tablespoonfuls in hot shortening.
Brown on both sides.

title: impossible tuna and cheddar pie(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch glass pie plate. In skillet, cook onions and margarine until light brown.
Sprinkle tuna, 1 cup of cheese and onions in pie plate.
Beat eggs, milk, baking mix and pepper in blender or with wire whisk 1 minute. Pour into pie plate or square dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Top with tomato slices and remaining cheese.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Cook 5 minutes, then serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Place about half the potatoes in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Put about half the cheese, half the milk and half the soup on top.
Then make second layer the same way.
Place the strips of cheese on top of the layered ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grits casserole
directions: Combine grits and water and cook slow about 25 or 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
As soon as this begins to thicken, stir in the remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes large amount.

title: oatmeal candy
directions: Add the first 4 ingredients together in medium saucepan. Begin cooking on medium heat.
Meanwhile, put a cube of ice in water in small bowl.
Also, prepare a platter or cake pan with butter or lay out plastic wrap for the drop method.
Stir while cooking.
When candy forms a soft ball in ice water, add last 4 ingredients, stirring quickly.
Remove from heat.
Quickly drop from spoon (to look like round cookies) or pour all in a cake pan and cut when cooled.
If you have a large family, it's best to double this recipe.

title: skillet fudge
directions: Put all ingredients, except vanilla and pecans in a large iron skillet.
Cook and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Let come to a full boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir occasionally.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Let cool until ready to drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased waxed paper.

title: squash casserole #1
directions: Cook squash and onion in water until tender and almost dry. Add margarine and mash.
Add eggs, milk, sugar, crackers, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add cheese.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Add the 1/4 cup crumbs and some pats of margarine.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Let stay in oven until crumbs are browned.
Serves 6 or more.

title: hot tamales
directions: Cook beef in small amount of lard for 10 to 15 minutes; add onions and garlic continuing to cook.
Season to taste with salt, red pepper and chili powder; add tomato paste.
Cook until all ingredients are done.
Let meat set for a few minutes; remove fat from top.
Make a mush by pouring boiling water over cornmeal; season to taste.
Spread mush over shucks.
Place thick line of meat in center of mush and roll up.
Place in large cooker or Dutch oven.
Pour in 3 cups boiling water.
Cover and cook slowly for 3 hours.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate vegetables.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and vinegar. Pour over cabbage, carrots and onion and let sit in refrigerator for a couple of hours.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Combine all ingredients and pour over beef in heavy pan.
Cover and cook slowly 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
When thoroughly cooked, remove any remaining fat. Separate beef by shredding in sauce.
Serve on buns.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine egg, sugar, milk and shortening.
Mix well and pour into waxed paper, lined 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon flour evenly over dough.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, then drain and crumble.
Brown the ground beef with the onion added.
Saute until the onion is tender.
Drain.
Mix the catsup, salt, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Combine beans, meats and catsup mixture in a greased 2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Put oatmeal, boiling water and oleo in bowl.
Cover and let stand 20 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and flour.
Mix slowly.
Pour in greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Add icing.
Return to oven until topping bubbles and is brown.

title: baked squash
directions: Boil squash, salt and onion until tender.
Put in pepper and cheese and mix.
Put into casserole; add cracker crumbs and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Saute onion with butter.
Add bacon and brown with garlic clove.
Add MBT beef and simmer (approximately 15 to 20 minutes). Beat eggs.
Toss all ingredients with cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with parsley and cheese.
Enjoy.

title: spicy pork chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown pork and onions until pork is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in the garlic, peppers and celery; cook for 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings (2 1/2 quarts).

title: poppin fresh barbecue cups
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add sauce and onions.
Separate biscuits and place one in each of 12 ungreased muffin cups, pressing dough up the sides of the edge of the cup.
Spoon meat into cups; add dash of Mexican hot sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until biscuits are browned.

title: pot roast
directions: In 6-quart saucepan, brown roast on all sides.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low; cover.
Cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover; cook 45 minutes or until meat and vegetables are fork-tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Stir together flour and remaining 1/4 cup water.
Gradually stir into soup mixture.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix melted butter, milk, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Break up slices of bread and place in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Pour the mixture over bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugars and eggs.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Slowly add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon torte
directions: Cut butter into flour and nuts until well blended.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Combine cream cheese, 10x and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust. Cook puddings with 3 cups milk just until boiling.
Spread on cream cheese layer.

title: milk shake
directions: Put milk, sweetener and orange juice concentrate or fruit in blender.
Blend while adding ice cubes, one at a time.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Scald the milk.
Add sugar, fat and salt; let cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast, dissolved in 1/4 cup water.
Mix with enough flour to make a soft dough that can be handled.
Knead lightly a few minutes to obtain a smooth surface.
Place dough in well-greased bowl.
Cover with cloth.
Place bowl in warm area; allow to rise until dough has doubled in size.
Shape into rolls; place in greased pan.
Allow to rise.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: french bread pizza
directions: Assemble on the day it is served.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large mixing bowl, cut butter or shortening into flour with fork or pastry blender until crumbly. Stir in milk until just sticking in one ball (sometimes takes less milk).

Turn onto floured board and knead 10 to 12 times. Roll or press the dough to 3/4-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutters. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Take 2 pieces of bread, put peanut butter on it, then put jelly on it.
Put 2 pieces together, then you put it in your mouth and bite down and chew and swallow.

title: baked seafood casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine crab meat, shrimp, mayonnaise, green peppers, celery, onion, salt, pepper, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauces.
Place in a buttered casserole.
Top with chips and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to creamed mixture with orange juice.
Add coconut and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: lemon-coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions; pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake as directed.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with coconut while warm.
Bring sugar and milk to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; spoon over warm cake.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients.
Spread and seal with mayonnaise, then top with sugar, Parmesan cheese and bacon in that order.
Seal with aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight or for 12 hours. Serve as is; do not stir.
This will last for 2 to 3 days if refrigerated.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook all ingredients until small amount forms a ball in cup of cold water.
Beat egg whites.
Test syrup; if forms ball in cup of cold water, pour 1/2 syrup mixture over egg whites.
Cook remaining syrup until small amount forms hard ball in cup of cold water.
Continue beating first mixture constantly.
Pour remaining syrup mixture over first mixture.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Chopped nuts may be added before dropping.
Does not do well in rainy weather.

title: turkey parmesan
directions: Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Dip turkey slices in eggs, then coat well with bread crumbs and cheese.
Spray bottom of baking dish with Pam.
Cover bottom with sauce and add breaded turkey slices.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and spoon a little more sauce and cover with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes to 1/2 hour in 400° oven.
Serve with spaghetti.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add marshmallows.
Pour in prepared tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy lemon cheese cake
directions: Measure 1 cup of mix (set aside).
Combine remaining mix with egg and oil.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips, milk and margarine in large saucepan. Let cool 5 minutes, then fold in peanuts and marshmallows. Drop by spoon onto waxed paper. Waxed paper may be coated with butter.

title: pecan bar cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk together.
Measure flour and cinnamon; stir into butter mixture.
Pat into a lightly greased 10 x 13-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat water and egg white until frothy. Brush over dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown.
Cut right away.
Makes about 50 bars.

title: eggnog cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer, add eggnog, vanilla and yolks.
Beat until smooth. Add flour mixture and beat on low until combined.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet, 1 inch apart.
Sprinkle lightly with more nutmeg.
Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: banana split brownies
directions: Bake brownies as directed on box.
Cool.
Slice bananas and cover top of brownies.
Spread Cool Whip on top of bananas.
Add cherries, one for each square to be cut.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: ham bomb
directions: Dice all ingredients and place in large casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until carrots are tender.

title: banana berry shake
directions: In blender or food processor, combine all ingredients; blend until smooth.
Makes 1 (1 2/3-cup) serving.

title: potato and spinach
directions: Heat oil in a pot.
Add onion, potato slices, salt, cumin and hot pepper.
Saute and cover on medium heat for 15 minutes.
Add spinach and cover again for 15 to 20 minutes.
When potatoes are tender, the dish is ready to eat.
Serves 6.

title: knorr spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours and stir well before serving.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve with rippled potato chips or for spreading on pumpernickel bread.
(Most people who don't like spinach still like this dip!)

title: apple pan dainties
directions: Cream together shortening, eggs and sugar.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Combine and add apples.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix mushroom soup and milk and pour over chicken.
In bowl, mix melted margarine, stuffing mix and cream of celery soup.
Add broth until mixture is a nice, moist consistency.
Put stuffing over top of chicken. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: waldorf slaw salad
directions: When you're tired of salads that taste like an afterthought, try this twist on a great American classic.
Combine cabbage, apple chunks and raisins.
Pour on slaw dressing and toss gently to coat everything with its delicious, tangy flavor.
Chill to let flavors blend.
Before serving, garnish with more apple slices and chopped walnuts.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add sugar slowly.
Add other ingredients and bake in unbaked pastry shell at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mini burgers
directions: In 3 small bowls, divide icing.
Tint one yellow, one red and leave the third white.
Tint the coconut green.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook and drain part of juice of tomatoes.
Cook celery, onions and bell peppers with tomatoes for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often. Dissolve in vinegar.
Pour over tomatoes, etc. and cook another 1 1/2 hours, until thick.
Cool and put in sterilized jars.

title: glorified mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Boil until tender; drain.
Soften cream cheese.
Beat cheese and sour cream together until blended. Gradually add hot potatoes to mixture.
Beat until fluffy.
Add seasonings.
Put in 2-quart dish. Dot with oleo.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and mix with softened cream cheese.
Add onion, pimento and sauce.
Mix well.
Form into ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: shortcut sauerbraten
directions: Cut roast into 1 1/2 to 2-inch thick strips.
Brown meat.
In small bowl, combine gravy, water and vinegar.
Pour over meat. Cover and simmer for 1 hour; cook evenly.
Remove meat; set aside. Add gingersnaps.
Cook until it thickens, stirring.
Do not dissolve; strain gravy, then add meat.
Serve over noodles. Serves 6.

title: onion-beef casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Stir in soup mix, flour, tomato sauce and water. Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in macaroni.
Turn into casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and one stick margarine and spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese, one stick margarine and confectioners sugar.
Spread over wafer crust.
Add bananas (sliced), drained pineapple, Cool Whip, nuts and cherries over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave pizza
directions: On two 9-inch plates covered with wax paper, press half of dough to form a 9-inch circle.
Press perforations together to seal.
Brush each lightly with cooking oil.
Microwave one pizza at a time at Medium-high for 4 minutes.
Flip dough over and carefully remove waxed paper.
Microwave on Medium-high 3 to 3 1/2 minutes more, until set and crisp.
There will be some brown spots.
Divide tomato sauce evenly between the 2 crusts, spreading to edge.
Add toppings on both and sprinkle with cheese. Microwave at Medium-high 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove immediately for crisper crust.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press rolls on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit ice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer 30 to 45 minutes before serving.
Serve while slushy. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: italian tortellini soup
directions: Remove casing from sausage; brown with onion and garlic.
Add next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes. Skim fat from soup. Add remaining ingredients; simmer, covered, for additional 35 to 40 minutes.

title: creamy crab and artichoke dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Blend cream cheese and mayo until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients and place in glass pie pan. Bake 15 to 18 minutes until brown and heated through. Serve with crackers, warm.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Freeze in an electric freezer.

title: old-fashioned apple butter
directions: Core and slice apples, do not peel.
Add enough water to cook apples until soft.
Press through sieve and measure.
Bake in oven in large roaster pan, stirring several times.
Bake until mixture remains in a smooth mass when a little is cooled.
When the apple butter is about ready to can, put the red hots in, after they have melted, pour into sterilized jars and seal while hot.
Keep oven at 325°.

title: crab meat bake
directions: Put layers of crab meat in buttered baking dish.
Cover each layer of crab meat with crumbs and add dots of butter.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking sheet.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt in medium bowl.
Using a pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter and shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in enough milk to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto a lightly floured surface.
Knead dough lightly. Roll out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into biscuit rounds with a two inch cutter. Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: transparent pie or tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken dice casserole
directions: Blend together milk and soup.
Mix all other ingredients in a large casserole dish (except bread crumbs).
Stir in soup mixture. Refrigerate for 8 hours.
Top with bread crumbs and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, until bubbly.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients until moistened, then beat for 2 minutes.
Add egg whites; beat for another 5 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom wiese's goulash
directions: Chop onion and pepper.
Saute in low-fat oil.
Add ground beef.
Brown.
Season with salt, pepper, etc.
Add tomatoes; cook for 5 minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles in casserole and mix well.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°. Feeds 6 to 8.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into a casserole.
Place casserole in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Grease pie plate and fill 2/3 full with sliced apples.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over apple slices.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Quick, easy and delicious.

title: skillet sauerbraten
directions: Brown meat.
Add celery.
Cook until done.
Add red wine, water and onion soup.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add gingersnaps.
Mix. Then add carrots and limas.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Put into boiling water and let come to a boil.
Drain.
Dip each slice in olive oil and roll in Italian bread crumbs.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: shelia's cornbread dressing
directions: Make cornbread according to recipe. Make roux (oil, flour and onions). Add mushroom soup. Boil giblets and grind (save broth to mix with cornbread and seasonings) until soft. Salt and pepper to taste. Add egg, parsley and garlic. Bake in greased casserole dish at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: fruited jello salad
directions: Make jello, using water/fruit juice mixture.
Add fruit to jello and refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and melt butter.
Then add all ingredients and mix well.
Add pecans and blend well.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 375° for about 55 minutes.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: Spread crescent rolls into a 10-inch pie plate.
Baste with a thin layer of mustard and let dry.
Cook and stir zucchini, onion and margarine (about ten minutes).
Add parsley flakes, salt, pepper, basil, oregano, eggs and Mozzarella cheese.
Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for about 20 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake, just until filling has set.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting and serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas with a fork.
Stir in ingredients and pour into a buttered loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
This can be frozen after baked.

title: vegetable salad
directions: To make dressing, in a medium saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
In a large bowl, combine peas, corn, beans and remaining ingredients.
Add dressing and toss until vegetables are coated.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Stir occasionally.

title: barbecued chicken sauce
directions: Dip chicken halves in sauce.
Place on broiler.
Turn and baste every 10 minutes for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes enough sauce for 5 broiler halves.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
On top of stove, bring to boil the water, cocoa and 2 sticks margarine.
Pour over flour mix and blend.
Add beaten eggs, sour cream and baking soda.
Put in big cookie sheet pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Boil cranberries (will pop when done), sugar and water until done, stir in jello until dissolved.
Stir in marshmallows and other ingredients place in mold and chill.

title: spaghetti sauce with mushrooms
directions: Cook onion and meat in olive oil and add all other ingredients and cook slowly for at least 3 hours.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Melt margarine or butter.
Mix dry ingredients and add eggs, syrup and melted margarine.
Beat well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Pour hot frosting on hot cake.

title: fancy chicken
directions: Cover 13 x 9 pan with 12 pieces of chicken breasts.
Lay strips of Swiss cheese on chicken, then Cheddar cheese.
Then Mozzarella cheese.	Mix cream of chicken soup with water.
Pour over chicken with cheese.
Sprinkle dry mix of Pepperidge Farm herb stuffing mix and top with stick of melted margarine.
Bake at 325° for about 2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 40 minutes at 450°.

title: peanut butter raisin squares
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar to boiling in heavy 2-quart saucepan, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter. Pour over cereal and raisins; stir until well coated.
Press into ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 24 squares.

title: easy oven pot roast
directions: Dust roast in flour.
Brown on all sides in hot oil in a Dutch oven.
Spread soy sauce and pepper on all sides of roast.
Add water and bay leaf.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: oven fries
directions: Cut potatoes in quarters and place on baking sheet.
Brush with olive oil.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Microwave 2 minutes; stir. Microwave one minute more.
Add vanilla and nuts at end of microwaving.
Turn out onto greased cookie sheet and chill.

title: cornbread a'la brig
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix everything in big bowl.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
To reduce size of bread, use 3/4 cup corn meal, flour and milk.
All other measurements remain the same.

title: fruit fluff
directions: Cream together the pineapple and pudding.
Stir in fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges.
Blend in Dream Whip.
Chill.

title: cajun-style chicken nuggets
directions: Combine onion soup mix, bread crumbs, chili powder, cumin, thyme and pepper. Dip chicken in bread crumb mix, coating well. Place on greased pan and drizzle with 2 or 3 tablespoons oil. Cook until done.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Put in double boiler. Cook until creamy, stirring all the time. Before serving, add whipped cream (1/2 pint).

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Add all ingredients, but cheese.
Mix.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Add grated cheese last 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients in a refrigerator jar.
Marinate until ready to eat, about 5 days.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Dissolve sugar in liquid before adding dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: 3 loaves.
If 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans are used, it yields 2 loaves.

title: harvest dinner
directions: Brown hamburger, then layer hamburger, potatoes, carrots and onions in roaster until all are used.
Add corn; pour tomatoes over and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: cinnamon kuchen
directions: Scald milk with butter.
Add salt and sugar to milk.
When milk is lukewarm, add yeast (mixed in lukewarm water to dissolve), then add egg and mix well.
Last add flour and raisins.
Knead enough to make a soft ball (not sticky).
Works well in large Tupperware bowl.
Let rise until double, then put in 2 round cake pans.
Let rise half again the size.
Top with melted butter or margarine and add cinnamon and sugar.
Can put a crumb crust on top as for apple crumb pie.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: impossible ham 'n swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with handbeater. Pour into plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soy chicken wings
directions: Place chicken wings in baking dish.
Make sauce out of other ingredients and pour over wings.
Bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven. Turn wings and bake 30 minutes more.

title: zucchini-tomato skillet
directions: Cook onion in butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add zucchini and mushrooms; cook, stirring often, 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes; cook 1 minute, stirring often.
Drain vegetables and return to skillet; gently stir in parsley and next 5 ingredients. Cook 1 minute or until thoroughly heated.
Remove skillet from heat.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover and let stand 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Cook hamburger until no longer pink. Saute cut up celery and onion in pan where hamburger was. Combine ingredients in a large baking dish. Cook 45 minutes in 350° oven. Sprinkle 1 can chow mein noodles over top. Put back in oven at 400° until noodles are slightly brown.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake as directed on cake box.
While cake is warm, mix powdered sugar with a little orange juice and pour over cake.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix ingredients together except chips and nuts.
Pour in greased 2 x 13-inch pan.
Top with butterscotch chips and chopped nuts.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: famous famous fudge
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil for 2 minutes the sugar, milk, butter and vanilla.
Add the marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add the milk chocolate and semi-sweet chocolate chips and keep stirring until melted.
Add in the nuts; distribute well through the fudge.
Spread out on buttered cookie sheet; chill and cut into bite size pieces.

title: almond rusks
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add slightly beaten eggs, cream and chopped nuts.
Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Chill.
Roll into 4 long narrow rows 17 inches long. Place on buttered 17 x 11-inch pan.
Brush with slightly beaten egg whites and sprinkle generously with pearl sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Slice and dry quickly in 350° oven on both sides.

title: monroe pizza
directions: Brown beef and sausage; drain.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Melt together in skillet until smooth.
Add other ingredients and spread on cocktail rye bread.

title: grandma's sour cream cake
directions: Grease and dust with flour an 8-inch square pan. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Save 1 cup of juice.
Make jello according to directions except use the 1 cup juice instead of 2nd cup of water. Blend in mayo.
Pour into a mold.
Add chopped pecans, cherries, pineapple and cheese.
Refrigerate.
Remove from mold.
Cover with Cool Whip and garnish with pecans, cherry halves and shredded cheese.

title: egg salad sandwiches with bacon, mustard and green onions
directions: Mix together eggs, celery, onions, parsley, bacon, mayonnaise and mustard in large bowl.
Place 4 slices toast on individual plates.
Evenly divide egg salad over toast; top with remaining slices.
Garnish with lettuce and tomato slices.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread dough.
Cut loaf in half.
Roll each half like a jelly roll.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Place one layer of pepperoni on top of dough; cover with a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and roll like a jelly roll. Bake approximately 1 hour.

title: mrs. bartlett's banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift flour and soda and add to mixture.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes in buttered pan.
Can be frozen.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Spray 2-quart oblong baking dish with vegetable cooking spray. Arrange chicken, bone side down, in dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine soup and water; spoon over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.
Serve with pasta.

title: slaw
directions: Mix and bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and mustard seed.
Remove from heat and add cabbage, pepper and onion. Refrigerate.
This will keep for several weeks in the refrigerator.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Measure out ingredients first and butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine, in a 3-quart saucepan, the sugar and corn syrup.
Heat over moderate heat, stirring often, until it starts to bubble. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until well mixed.
Add Rice Krispies and stir until well blended.
Press into buttered pan using a buttered spatula, wax paper or buttered fingers.

title: blueberry swirl
directions: Blend butter, flour and pecans; press into 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread this onto the crust.
Swirl pie filling on top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine first three ingredients. Put in a 9 by 13 inch glass casserole dish. Top with cheese slices then tater tots. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Do not beat.
Just stir until well blended.
Bake at 325° in a Bundt pan about 1 hour and 10 minutes or longer, if needed.
Cool and add cream cheese frosting.

title: pistoleros
directions: Brown hamburger.

Add Tony Chachere to taste. Chop the broccoli finely. Drain meat and add broccoli and Velveeta cheese. Mix well. Set aside. Cut off one end of the roll; dredge out the inside of the roll to make a cavity. Stuff the roll with meat mixture. Brush the top of the roll with the garlic-butter mixture. Cook at 350° until rolls are browned.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Toss in bowl the hash browns, melted margarine and onions. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: aunt helen's fun cookies
directions: Stir together first 3 ingredients. Add your creation of favorites. Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon (do not mash flat). Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until lightly brown at edges. Cool on rack.

title: sticky buns
directions: Thaw bread and break or slice into small pieces.
Make them uniform size, so they rise evenly.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix together all ingredients, allow garlic bud to marinate 3 days then remove.
Shake well before serving.
Excellent on lettuce wedges or for taco salad dressing.

title: little french peas
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in saucepan; add the peas (slightly defrosted), peeled onions and the lettuce heart cut in shreds. Sprinkle parsley, chervil, sugar and salt over the peas and stir thoroughly until butter is melted well over the peas, then add chicken base in 1/4 cup water to the peas.
Heat thoroughly and add 1 tablespoon of butter and serve.

title: turkey stuffing(10 to 12 pound bird)
directions: Put bread stuffing in a large bowl.
Add lukewarm water, enough to make moist mixture.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add egg, parsley, onion, poultry spice, salt, pepper and sausage.
Mix sausage in, using hands to mix well.
Wash turkey cavity with warm water.
Shake salt into cavity and rinse with cold water.
Fill both ends with stuffing.
Sew with button thread.
Tie wings and legs together.
Place on greased rack in pan.
Place salt pork on turkey using toothpicks.
Add small amount of water.
Cover with lid or foil.
Baste 2 or 3 times while cooking.
Take foil off the last 3/4 hour of baking to brown well.
Bake in a 275° to 325° oven, 4 to 4 1/2 hours for 10 to 12 pound bird.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, onion,
pepper,
sugar, salt and flour; beat eggs and add
to squash. Add butter.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto oiled griddle or frying pan.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans together.
Then press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, then cool.
Mix Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese; spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk until thickened, then spread over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and chill for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Keep refrigerated.

title: spiced pecans
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Beat egg white until stiff.
Coat pecans with egg white; add cinnamon mixture.
Coat nuts.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: lobster, avocado and asparagus saladvinaigrette and lobster-infused oil
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Whisk oils in slowly. Season with salt.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbows.
Melt butter; add salt, mustard and onions. Blend well.
Add milk; stir constantly until mixture comes to boil.
Sauce will not be thick.
Remove from heat; add cheese. Stir until cheese has blended into milk.
Pour over elbows in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: lucy's oven fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Dip chicken in beaten egg; roll in potato flakes.
Place in oil or drippings (use iron skillet).
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 20 to 30 minutes longer.

title: pecan roll
directions: Cook butter, sugar and dates until thick.
Add vanilla and pecans and stir well.
Roll in wet towel and chill until firm; slice thinly.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: In stockpot, heat oil.
Add bacon.
Saute until golden.
Add carrots, onion and garlic.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes until soft. Add broth, tomatoes with juice and seasonings.
Heat to boiling; add pasta.
Cover.
Cook 15 minutes or until pasta is al dente. Add chickpeas, their liquid and kale; heat through.
Pass cheese.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Spray 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Stir and freeze.

title: macaroni and cheese and tomato
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to directions; drain.
Add 1 teaspoon oleo to hot, drained macaroni.
Stir in undrained tomatoes and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts and is stringy. Stir once.

title: gourmet stew
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Put all ingredients into casserole dish and mix well.
Cover and bake 3 hours.
Casserole should go right from oven to table.
Serve with crusty bread, tossed salad and a good wine.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Toss ingredients with an assortment of chopped vegetables (tomatoes, onions and cucumbers) and pieces of cheese.
Serve cold.

title: homemade butter
directions: Let margarine and buttermilk set out until room temperature. Mix together with mixer.
Store in refrigerator.

title: clam chowder
directions: In pot, heat 1/2 cup oil. Add clams and onions. Cover and let simmer in own juice and oil. Stir every 5 minutes. When clams begin to stick to pot, add tomatoes and 3 cups water. Bring to slow boil. Cook for 1/2 hour. Stir every 10 minutes. Add water to keep clams from sticking. Add potatoes; cook 1/2 hour more.

title: chocolate quad cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: pasty pie
directions: Mix together the meat, potato and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Put in pie pan and add the water.
Cover with pie crust and flute edges.
Punch one hole in the center top.
Bake for 1 hour in a 375° oven.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour into vegetables, stirring gently to blend well.
Cover and chill 24 hours.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: canned corn
directions: Cut off corn and add 1 teaspoon salt per jar.
Boil 3 hours.

title: topsy turvy dates(this is a great recipe for dates.)
directions: Break dates into a 9-inch round cake pan or baking dish.
Add butter and 1 cup of boiling water.
Stir to melt butter and soften dates.
Add egg, flour, sugar and brown sugar; mix well.
Add baking soda, baking powder, salt and nuts; thoroughly mix with a fork until well blended.
Slowly pour
remaining boiling water (1 1/2 cups) over entire mixture.
Bake 4 minutes in a 375° oven. Serve with ice cream piled in center.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and 1 cup sugar in large bowl. Add eggs, 1 at a time, until well mixed. Next, add vanilla.

title: methodist hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; add rest of the ingredients.
Put into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix the above ingredients and add garlic salt and seasoned salt to taste.
Spread on 5 floured tortillas.
Roll the tortilla and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Cut into pinwheels and place on serving tray.
Serve salsa on the side.

title: low-fat goulash
directions: Cook and drain ground round. Cook and drain macaroni.
Put all ingredients in saucepan.
Heat over medium heat.

title: grandmother's corn relish
directions: Peel and chop the onions and tomatoes.
Cut corn from cob.
Mix all ingredients and cook slowly until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Do not let it stick.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: honey dijon chicken and fettuccine
directions: Combine broth, mustard, honey and cornstarch in a small bowl; mix until smooth. Transfer to a skillet and add chicken breasts, bell peppers and onion. Heat to a gentle boil; reduce to low. Cover and cook for 10 minutes or until sauce is thickened, vegetables are tender and chicken is heated through. Serve over hot fettuccine.

title: dutch apple pie
directions: You will also need a 9 1/2-inch pie pan.

title: super easy mexican dip
directions: Soften and spread cream cheese on bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Spread chili; pour salsa and top with cheese.
Add olives or peppers if desired.
Bake in oven or microwave until cheese is fully melted.
Serve with large tortilla chips.

title: marble cake
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Make a well and add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat well until creamy.
Stir in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: fried egg roll
directions: Slice potatoes into thin strips and fry.
Set aside.
Cut vegetables into small pieces.
Saute garlic, onion, pork and shrimp.
Season with salt and stir; add 1/4 cup water.
Cover and half cook it.
Add fried potatoes; drain, then wrap.
Fry until brown.

title: boiled country cabbage
directions: Combine the onions,
green pepper, carrot, bacon or ham bits, salt and sugar.
Add
to the boiling water.
Cook for 10 minutes. Add chopped
cabbage
and cook for 20 to 25 minutes. A small amount of
water
may
have
to be added if cabbage is going to be cooked longer.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick chicken pie
directions: Mix 1/3 cup of broth and flour well.
Add 2 2/3 cups broth and 1/2 stick margarine (melted).
Add chicken.
Place in Pyrex dish and put in oven until mixture begins to bubble.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and work dough thoroughly.
Pinch off and form into balls (small or large as desired).
Place in a 375° preheated oven until brown, approximately 10 to 12 minutes.

title: french onion dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, cover and chill.
Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: butter bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook the sausage and onion until sausage is done. Drain off fat. To sausage, add undrained beans, milk, soup, salt, thyme and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Top with more sliced green onions, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon bun cake
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon together; set aside.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil the chicken until done.
Let cool and cut up in bite size pieces.
Add onion to butter and melt, then add chicken and let simmer 10 minutes.
Add soup and season to taste.
Let simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or dressing.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream 2 cups sugar with butter.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Mix flavoring and soda with sour cream and add alternately with dry ingredients and the creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites with remaining cup of sugar and fold into batter.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
(You do not have to grease pan.)

title: fudge
directions: Mix butter, milk, sugar and salt in pan.
Bring to boil.
Let boil 6 minutes, then pour over marshmallows and chocolate chips. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour onto cookie sheet; freeze until set.

title: crab dip
directions: Press cream cheese flat onto a plate.
Drain crab meat and spread across cream cheese.
Spread cocktail sauce over crab meat. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mold into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Top with cranberry sauce the last 15 minutes of baking.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar with cranberries; let stand 1 hour.
Add the pineapples and cranberries to the whipped cream and marshmallows. Let stand overnight.
Add nuts.
White grapes may also be used.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; mix with sugar and 1 cup water.
Set overnight.
Soften jello in orange juice for 5 minutes.
Add hot water to dissolve.
Add cranberry mixture, pineapple, celery, pecans and apples.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and extract; beat until creamy.
Mix together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend the 2 mixtures together.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll; cut into shapes.
Bake
at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and bouillon crystals and beat well with mixer.
Add Colby cheese and mix by hand.
Add chiles, lemon juice, Tabasco and chopped green onions.
After this is mixed, add peeled, chopped tomato.
Fold into mixture.
Chill.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Melt butter, sugar, corn syrup and salt on high on stove until bubbly around edges.
Lower temperature to medium and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add peanuts and soda.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Pour the mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: In skillet, cook onion in reserved drippings until tender. Stir in water, rice, bouillon and bay leaf; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in chopped pepper and bacon; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until rice is tender.
Spoon rice into pepper halves to serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: coconut pecan cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, oil and eggs.
Beat at med speed for 4 mins.
Stir in coconut & pecans.
Pour into 3 greased floured 9 inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 mins.

title: royal green bean casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and layer in order given in a 2 1/2-quart dish.
Mix together soup and sour cream and spread over top of vegetables.
Crush one package of Town House crackers.
Sprinkle over top.
Add cheese.
Melt butter; drizzle over top.
Can be prepared night before and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach-feta quiche
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain spinach thoroughly, pressing out excess water.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in butter.
Combine with spinach.
Add remaining ingredients into mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Saute minced onion in margarine.
Mix with other vegetables. Add mushroom soup and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crab-cheese dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, gradually adding cream.
Beat until smooth. Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and pepper. Remove bony bits from crab meat.
Stir into creamed cheese mixture.

title: apple-dee-lite
directions: Put apples in buttered baking pan, then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour water into this.
Mix margarine, sugar and flour until it's crumbly and sprinkle this over apples.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix sugar, flour, egg, pineapple juice and vinegar.
Cook over low heat until thick; cool.
Dice apples and mix in nuts and pineapple.
Pour into cool syrup.
Mix in Cool Whip and chill.

title: blue lemon fizz drink
directions: Pour lemonade into 1-quart pitcher. Add club soda or seltzer. Stir until lemonade is melted. Add blue food coloring and stir well.
Serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Peel and slice fruit.
Blend yogurt and cream cheese in blender until blended well.
Fold in fruit or blended mixture can be used as a fruit dip on the side.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook sugar, milk, flour and egg yolk at low heat until it becomes thick.
When it thickens, add vanilla, bananas and peanuts.

title: streusel-filled coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and egg together thoroughly.
Stir in milk.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in mixture.

title: jello cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Stir until well blended. Add pineapple and top with whipped topping.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat slowly.
Add next 6 ingredients to meat and simmer uncovered until thick.
Cook noodles until tender, drain and rinse in cold water.
In separate bowl, combine cottage cheese with next 4 ingredients.
Spoon small amount of meat mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish. Place a single layer of noodles in dish; spread 1/2 of cottage cheese mixture over noodles.
Add 1/2 of Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 of meat mixture.
Repeat layers, starting with lasagna noodles. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Line
pie
pan with crushed vanilla wafers.
Also stand wafers up	the
side
of the pie pan.
In a big bowl, stir the Eagle Brand
milk and lime juice.
After this is mixed really well, fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour into dish and refrigerate. It is best to make this a day in advance.

title: rye bread
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Stir to dissolve.
In mixing bowl, combine milk, salt, anise and molasses.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add rye flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in yeast mixture.
Slowly blend in remaining flour until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough onto floured surface. Knead 5 to 10 minutes or until smooth and elastic and does not stick when pinched with fingers.
Cover with waxed paper, then a towel.
Let rest 20 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Dip chicken in butter.
Set remaining butter aside.
Roll chicken in crumbs.
Place skin side up, in a 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
To leftover butter, add remaining ingredients. Pour over baked chicken.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add cold water to measure 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl.
Stir in liquid reserve.
Refrigerate 1 1/4 hours or until slightly thickened.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth. Refrigerate 10 minutes or until mixture will mound.
Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into 6-cup mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Turn fire low and add the rest of the ingredients; stir well. Cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil and pineapple juice on high speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, place pineapple rings on bottom and sides.
Cut butter in slices; place on pineapple.
Mix pineapple liquid with brown sugar.
Pour over pineapple in pan. Pour cake mixture over pineapple.
Place in 350° preheated oven. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown and will spring back with light touch.

title: curry sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in oil.
Add diced potatoes and carrot.
When potatoes start to change color slightly, add 6 cups water; bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender (about 10 minutes).
While potatoes are cooking, beat until smooth flour, curry powder and 1 1/4 cups water.
When potatoes are tender, add salt, thinly sliced onion and curry mixture, stirring until smooth. Serve over hot white rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together, reserving 1 cup pecans.
Roll in reserved pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, cream, sugar, salt and vanilla in a bowl and mix thoroughly.
Pour into ice cream can.
Add condensed, sweetened milk and stir well.
Add dairy milk to fill line on ice cream can and stir.
Freeze up in ice cream maker and let stand about 45 minutes.
Serve with favorite toppings.

title: brown gravy
directions: Put oil in the frying pan; heat on medium until hot, then add flour.
Stir constantly until flour is brown.
Add water until it is the desired thickness.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: scalloped raw potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in thin, crosswise slices.
Reserve enough potatoes for a top layer.
Place 1/2 the potatoes in a buttered baking dish (1 1/2-quart).
Cover with 1/2 margarine (or butter) that is cut into small pieces or melted.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the flour and onion and salt and pepper to taste; repeat.
Top the dish with potatoes reserved for this.
Pour in milk until it can be seen between the pieces of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.	Uncover and bake for 1 hour longer or until tender and brown on top.
Shredded Cheddar cheese can been sprinkled on top for last few minutes of baking, if desired.

title: gingerbread with lemon sauce
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and sugar 12 cup Bundt cake pan. Blend cake mix (dry), water, molasses, margarine, eggs, ginger, allspice and cloves in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, until moistened.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl frequently, 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake as directed on cake mix package.
Cool 10 minutes and invert on wire rack.
Remove pan and cool cake completely.
Dust with powdered sugar, if desired. Serve with Lemon Sauce.

title: fruited corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare muffin mix according to package directions, stirring in mincemeat.
Fill greased or paper baking cup-lined muffin cups 1/2 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately turn out of pan; serve warm.
Makes 18 to 22 muffins.

title: clark gable's pork tenderloin
directions: Mix ketchup, brown sugar and mustard.
Pour over tenderloins, wrap in foil and bake at 275° for 2
1/2 hours.
Cool and slice very thin.
Serve with small rolls or biscuits.
Good party treat. Serves 50 or more for a cocktail buffet.

title: peanut butter faces
directions: On a slice of bread, spread peanut butter.
Cut a square of wax paper and roll into a cone. Fill with jam.
Using cone as a pastry bag, draw faces on peanut butter with jam.
Garnish with chips, if desired.

title: homemade veggie dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well; chill.
Serve with your favorite vegetables.
Keeps one week in refrigerator.

title: hoot owls
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter with brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Combine melted, cooled chocolate with baking soda.
Remove 2/3 dough mixture to floured surface.
Blend chocolate mixture into remaining 1/3 dough mixture.
Chill for easier handling.
Roll out half of light dough to 10 x 4 1/2-inch strip.
Shape half of chocolate dough into 10 x 2-inch strip; place on strip of light dough.
Mold light dough around dark; wrap in foil.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut into slices 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick; place 2 slices together on greased baking sheet to resemble an owl.
Pinch top corner of each slice to form ears.
Place a chocolate chip in center of each slice for eyes.
Press a whole cashew nut between slices for a beak.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use tube pan.
Set oven at 350°.
Mix white sugar, 2 tablespoons cinnamon and nutmeg in a plastic bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Shake biscuits in sugar mixture.
Stack them in a tube pan.
Heat margarine, 2 teaspoons cinnamon and brown sugar until sugar dissolves.
Do not boil.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, jello, water and oil together.
Add eggs one at a time and lemon extract.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Heat sugar and orange juice.
Pour over warm cake.
Punch top with fork so juice goes all over.
Sprinkle top with sifted powdered sugar for decoration.
No icing necessary.

title: marlie's blue chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle chicken with pepper and place in greased glass baking dish.
Spread generously with Blue cheese dressing.
Bake 35 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet-n-sour hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into bite-size pieces.
Marinate hot dogs in sauce overnight.
Heat in crock-pot.

title: butterfingers
directions: Cream well butter, sugar and brown sugar and blend in egg, peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats. Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle on entire package of chocolate chips over baked mixture and let stand 5 minutes.

title: cheese squares
directions: Mix by hand the first 3 ingredients, then add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. You will have to spread and pat with fingers as batter is stiff.

title: pepper relish
directions: Wash and cut the peppers in quarters.
Remove stem, seeds and white membranes.
Peel and quarter onions.
Put all through food chopper.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 15 minutes; drain. Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Boil 20 minutes and pack immediately into hot, sterilized jars.

title: parisian rice casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in margarine. Cook sausage until pink is gone.
Drain. Brown rice in sausage oil. Combine all ingredients and add water.
Bake at 350° until rice is tender.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit in a large bowl.
Pour orange juice over mixed fruit. Cover and refrigerate until chilled. Serve cold as a side dish or dessert.
If desired, top with plain vanilla yogurt or sherbet.
Makes 4 servings.

title: skillet barbecued pork chops
directions: In a large skillet, with a tight-fitting lid, brown chops in oil over medium heat, approximately 5 minutes on each side.
Drain off excess fat.

title: meat loaf muffins
directions: In muffin tin, add meat loaf once it's all mixed; half fill each muffin tin.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over meat loaf.
Add remaining meat loaf mixture on top of cheese.
Place in 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes.

title: magyai beef(hungarian)
directions: Pat meat dry with paper towel. Season with salt and pepper. Heat 2 tablespoons butter or oleo in a large skillet or wide pot. Saute meat quickly in single layer until browned on all sides. Transfer to platter. Brown remaining meat, adding more butter or oleo as needed.
Saute mushrooms in same skillet over low heat, adding additional butter or oleo, if needed. Transfer to a separate plate.
Melt additional 1 tablespoon butter or oleo in same skillet. Saute onions until clear, about 5 minutes.
Add to mushrooms. Add mustard and tomato paste to skillet. Stir to mix. Slowly stir in 2 cups beef broth to make a smooth sauce, scraping browned bits from bottom of skillet.
Stir in sherry and paprika. Return onions and mushrooms to skillet. Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Gradually stir 1 cup beef broth into sour cream bowl until mixture is smooth.
Pour into skillet, stirring constantly. Simmer 3 minutes. Add beef and noodles. Heat slowly to serving temperature.

title: microwave orange roughy sunshine
directions: In a shallow microwave dish, place fillets with thickest parts to outside edge of dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and brush over fillets.
Cover dish with plastic wrap turned back at one corner for venting.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes on High, rotating dish 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time.
Let stand 2 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and bone the chicken breasts.
Cook and drain the broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice. Arrange chicken and broccoli in layers in casserole.
Put the soup mix over all.
Mix the cheese and cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples with lemon juice.
Arrange apples in rows in 7 x 10-inch baking dish, sprayed with nonstick oil.

title: chicken pan pie
directions: Boil chicken with 1 stick butter, salt and pepper.
Save 1 1/2 cups broth.
Chop up chicken and place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Pour cream of chicken soup and 1 1/2 cups broth over chicken.
Pour on 1/2 stick butter and 2 cans Veg-All, drained.
Mix 1 1/2 cups milk and 1 1/2 cups Bisquick.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: nut crescents
directions: Cut butter into flour, using pastry cutter or 2 butter knives. Add sugar, water, vanilla and nuts.
Dough will be somewhat crumbly.
Push together and chill in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into crescents with your fingers.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 15 to 18 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil.
Sauce keeps well in refrigerator. Bake one cut up chicken or six to eight chicken breasts.
Place sauce on chicken and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve on rice or alone with vegetables.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix potatoes, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken pieces in egg; roll in potato mixture.
Place skin side up in pan.
Bake uncovered for 50 minutes or until thickest pieces are done and coating is crisp.
Bake approximately 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken salad in cantaloupe halves
directions: Cut cantaloupes in half; discard seeds and scoop out flesh with melon baller, leaving 1/2-inch thick shells.
Smooth ragged edges with spoon.
Combine the melon balls, diced chicken, celery, almonds, orange sections and grapes.
Chill.

title: sugar and spice on a bun
directions: Brown meat and onions and pepper in saucepan.
Add sauce. Serve over toasted bun or fluffy rice.
Green salad goes well with this.

title: fettuccine with garlic and red pepper oil
directions: Heat oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat; add red pepper and cook 2 minutes. Add garlic; saut 30 seconds or until garlic is lightly browned.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Yield: 6 servings.
Serving size: one cup.

title: mocha cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in chocolate and liqueur.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Serves 8.

title: jumbo cheese shells
directions: Cook shells halfway done; drain water.
In large bowl, mix onion, salt, pepper, seasoned salt, garlic, egg, Mozzarella, Parmesan, Ricotta, Cheddar and parsley. Stuff shells with mixture. Place in baking pan.
Pour spaghetti sauce over shells.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box.
Cool for about 5 minutes. Combine Cool Whip and condensed milk; stir in the chilled pudding mix.
Put vanilla wafers and pudding in layers along with the sliced bananas; top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with a few vanilla wafer crumbs.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in Crisco.
Brown ground beef in mixture.
Add tomatoes, rice or macaroni.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix.
Place in covered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Macaroni takes a little longer.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a small greased casserole dish or crock.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs.
Heat at 375° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Spread on crackers.

title: rye bread(swiss appetizers)
directions: Mix cream cheese and mustard on medium blend.
Blend in meat, cheese and onion; spread on toasted slices.
Place on cookie sheet and broil 2 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: ever-ready muffin mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a very large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Add beaten eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Batter will keep in fridge for 6 weeks.
Will make about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening (I use my hands).
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add yeast with buttermilk and soda to flour mixture.
Mix well with hands.
Turn dough on a floured board and knead for 3 or 4 minutes. I put dough in greased Tupperware bowl and seal.
Dough will keep for 5 or 6 days in refrigerator.
Just pinch off and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes when needed.
No need to let rise.

title: pickled asparagus
directions: Boil last 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pack asparagus in wide-mouth quart jars.
Pour hot liquids over asparagus in jars. Seal and process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix mix, eggs and oil.	Add choice of chips.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool before cutting.

title: low calorie fruit
directions: Save the juice from pineapple chunks.
Drain juice off of all the fruits.
Mix pineapple juice, pudding and Tang.
Stir in fruit and store in fridge.
Will keep 4 to 5 days.

title: yummy squash casserole
directions: Saute squash and onions in 2 tablespoons butter until soft. Mix egg, cheese, milk, 6 tablespoons butter, salt, pepper and 1/3 cracker crumbs in greased casserole dish.
Gently add sauteed mixture and cover with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
If top gets too brown, cover lightly with foil.

title: chicken pot stew
directions: Cut up chicken and put in crock-pot; cover with water.
When chicken is done, remove from broth.
Cook potatoes and onion in broth.
On stove top, add spices to taste.
Add drained corn and boned chicken.
Simmer for 20 minutes or so.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Take fat and bones out.
Break into small pieces and put in bottom of dish.
Combine celery soup, mushroom soup and sour cream.
Put this over chicken.
Crush one tube of Ritz crackers and pour this over soup mixture, plus 1/2 stick margarine, cut in small pieces.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in bottom of well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Add pineapple (not drained).
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pineapple.
Pour butter over cake mix.
Add coconut.
Sprinkle pecans over cake.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot broccoli dip(good for anniversary dances)
directions: Saute celery, onion and mushrooms lightly.
Combine sauteed mixture with drained cooked broccoli and the soup.
Melt cheese roll in double boiler.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Keep hot in chafing dish or crock-pot.
Serve with Melba toast or corn chips. Serves 20 +.

title: broccoli with eggs and cheese
directions: Cut broccoli into large serving pieces and steam until crisp-tender.
Arrange broccoli and eggs in a broiler-proof casserole.
Melt butter in a saucepan and add cornstarch, stir constantly for 2 minutes.
Add milk and stir constantly until thickened.
Add cheese and stir.
Pour sauce over broccoli and eggs and broil until the top is brown, about 3 to 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cream, and margarine and bring to a boil; boil on medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, marshmallow creme, vanilla, and nuts. Stir quickly before mixture cools; when well mixed, pour into a 12 x 9 inch pan that has been coated with margarine. Let cool and cut into small squares. Store in an airtight tin.

title: empress chicken wings(chinese)
directions: Remove chicken wings tips (save for stock).
Combine soy sauce, sherry, ginger and garlic in a large bowl.
Stir in chicken. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Stirring occasionally.
Remove chicken from bowl and save marinade.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Lightly coat chicken wings with cornstarch.
Add to skillet and brown on all sides.
Remove chicken from pan.
Drain off the fat.
Add 2/3 cup of water and left over marinade into pan.
Add chicken, green onions and slivered ginger over chicken.
Spread evenly.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes, onions and celery in chicken broth.
When they are done, add milk and flour, which have been made into a paste.
Stir well, then add Velveeta cheese.

title: annie's sweet potato roll
directions: Allspice may be substituted for flavorings.

title: souper cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine soup, eggs and milk.
Stir in muffin mix until blended.
Gently fold in sausage.
Into greased 9-inch square baking pan, pour muffin mixture.
Bake 20 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla, oil and zucchini.
Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix until all ingredients are well blended.
Add pineapple and pecans and mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate berry pie
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips and milk. Microwave on Medium for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds. Stir until chocolate is completely melted and smooth. Stir in vanilla. Pour chocolate into baked pie crust. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours until firm. Before serving, stir together Cool Whip, thawed berries and juice. Spread over chocolate layer. Garnish with chocolate nonpareils if desired. "Enjoy."

title: peanut apple pie meringue
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Line a 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons flour over bottom of crust.
Arrange apples alternately with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Add butter on top.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Rub
chicken
halves well with mixture of salts.
Brown well in
melted butter.
Prepare sauce for barbecue with other ingredients.
Pour over chicken placed breast down in roaster. Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours in oven at 325°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix juices and water in bowl.
Add sugar;
stir and add ice to cool.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck with onion.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes and chili seasoning.
Bring to a boil; immediately reduce heat to 250° and cook 1/2 hour, then turn heat down to simmer, and simmer an additional 45 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and grated Cheddar cheese.

title: white wonder cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Blend until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff enough to form peaks.
Fold into batter.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix eggs, milk, butter and vanilla together.
Then mix all of the dry ingredients to this.
Roll dough out on floured paper, about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut cookies out and bake at 400° until light brown. This recipe is great for Christmas cookies or any other holiday cut outs.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil after dredging in flour. Place in casserole or baking pan. To make sauce, saute onion, celery and pepper in drippings. Add catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce and brown sugar. Spoon over chicken. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350° or until tender.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy (5 to 7 minutes).
Add eggs (one at a time), beating well after each.
Gradually add flour; beat just until blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 15 minutes and remove from pan.
Cool completely.

title: hearty potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices. Arrange potato slices in a lightly greased 3-quart shallow baking dish. Combine 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons melted butter, paprika and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in a small bowl; stir well. Drizzle butter mixture over potato slices. Cover and bake at 425° for 30 minutes. Remove cover; bake an additional 15 minutes or until tender.

title: shark grilled with chinese seasonings
directions: Cut shark steaks in 4 to 6 equal portions.
Combine ginger, garlic, soy sauce, rice vinegar, sesame oil and hot oil in a glass or ceramic dish large enough to hold fish in a single layer.
Add fish.
Turn pieces once, cover and allow to marinate in refrigerator for an hour, turning them once or twice more.

title: squash patties
directions: Grate squash and drain for 30 minutes.
Mix together one-fourth cup, plus 2 tablespoons of flour.
Fry in 2 tablespoons oleo.

title: christmas pepper jelly
directions: Combine peppers and divide into 2 parts. In 1/2 of the peppers stir in 1 c. of sugar.
In a saucepan, combine the peppers and sugar mixture with vinegar and the remaining sugar; boil this for 10 minutes.
Add the other 1/2 of the peppers and pectin; boil for an additional 10 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.
Serve over crackers with cream cheese.
Yield: 8 cups.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups water.
Let set partially.
Mix other ingredients and add to partially set Jell-O.
Refrigerate. Great for the holidays!

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Place shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla in mixing bowl; beat thoroughly.
Sift together, flour, salt and soda.
Add to shortening mixture, mixing well.
Blend in oats and drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
For variety, add chopped nuts, raisins, chocolate chips or coconut to the dough.
Cool on cookie rack or wax paper.

title: cheesy bean dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in medium bowl.
Stir in chilies, onion and seasoning mix until smooth.
Spread half the mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer Monterey Jack cheese and Cheddar cheese over top.
Spread with remaining bean dip mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beef stroganoff
